title: Follow directions and you will love it!
text: Well as a TOTAL NEWBIE to this whole drone thing I have to admit I was a bit intimidated at first.  Read all the reviews on a MULTITUDE of drones and decided on the F11.  Was scared to death my little black beauty was going to fly away......still have it and have had several successful days.  Love the tips that I was sent for flying tips which explained why I lost control a couple times (stay away from trees that can block satellite connect, duh) and crashed (LOL) all turned out okay despite a scratch or two as expected in this learning phase.  However, it has peaked my dog's interest who thinks this mechanical black bird looks like it could be a lot of fun to chase!  Highly recommend the F11 as it is sturdy for the money apparently and a great learning drone with what seems to have a decent camera & video capabilities.  I have yet to totally master those skills.....ha, ha!

title: Misleading
text:
Great advertising. Wonderful reviews. Great packaging. Once it arrived I opened it, set it up, configured the drone. Anytime I need to connect Wi-Fi to something is when the issues begins. App wouldn‚Äôt connect. Drone and controller were paired. I was able to configure the gyroscope and calibrate. I took it outside and all I wanted to do was a simple up and down motion and the drone went crazy all over my backyard. Back in the box and a return label was printed. It‚Äôs not as simple as people here claim it to be. It doesn‚Äôt pair well with the app. Beautiful device, but for 300.00 I can‚Äôt risk replacing something if it lands upside somewhere and can‚Äôt fly back.

Update- 8/3/2022 I‚Äôve been flying drones for years so I know what I‚Äôm doing. Purchased this again and gave it another try. First day it was perfect. Second day there is lots of miscommunication, drone is spinning out of control and I‚Äôm in beginner mode to get used to this new product. Both are going back.

title: So far so good
text:
The preparation is a little more involved than I thought (this is my first drone), good thing the app does have a quick start screen with the steps so I don't have to carry the user's guide all the time.
The battery life is quite good, compared to other drones (I had shopped around to compare before purchasing the F11 Pro). The only problem I encountered was it doesn't know to avoid obstacles, so make sure you don't fly it too close to anything while not familiar with the remote control.
I've tested all the functionality, and they are all there, just make sure you stay in the Beginner mode until you're confortable enough with control the drone.
Charging the drone and the remote control is easy, as they both use the same charger (USB).

title: Easy To Learn

The camera is very good, but the angle controls are a little clumsy so it can take a little bit to get the camera shot just right. title: Amazing Fun! Great for new drone owners
text:

After the first flight I already feel ready to go back out and try the more advanced features again.

The 120 degrees really captures everything, and the flying is very stable. I love the altidude locking. The return home feature is perfect.

title: Steady in the air, looong battery life
text:
After going the cheap route - I earlier bought and quickly returned two under-$100 drones - I decided to get serious and spend a little more money for something that was more solid. I read and read ... and read, and became discouraged because it appeared as though I was going to have to spend $700+ (and probably $1,000+) to find a good drone with all of the features I wanted: high-resolution video and stills camera, good battery life, long range.

And then I found the Ruko F11 Pro, for an amateur price :). The reviews were consistent - this seemed like a professional quality drone for about $300. The battery has a 30-minute flight time, and it came with two batteries. It had all the features I wanted or needed as a beginner pilot.

The other drones I had bought immediately veered away on take off, finding the most convenient nearby tree to "hide" in. This Ruko F11 Pro drone was steady from the start: a straight-up take-off, even with a little wind. The remote control feels sturdy, and my phone connected easily to the app. The camera quality is awesome. I bought a little USB card reader that plugs in my computer so I can easily download the hi-res drone video footage.

My son and I have only flown it for one day, and we both had a great time. (Maybe dad had even more fun haha.) I have wanted a drone for awhile, and I am glad I spent a little bit more than the "toy drone" price range to find something that is a blast right out of the box. You can read and read and read like I did, or stop reading now and be happy with this purchase.

title: This Drone Has Everything You Need and a Little More
text: I‚Äôm so glad I purchased this drone instead of the DJI Mavic Mini for my son's first drone. I spent the better part of a day reading a learning a lot of information about drones. I also wanted to purchase a drone for him that he could possibly  use or get experience to use for recording football games since he also films for the high school football team. Video clarity and the stability overall while in the air was a major factor in my decision to purchase this drone. I watched a video that was recorded by another reviewer and after watching and reading other reviews and you tube videos, I quickly clicked out of the video and hit purchase! I almost caved and bought him the more expensive dji mavic mini and even with using the education discount combined with refurbished price it wasn‚Äôt worth it compared to the value and quality I feel this drone offers. My son is very pleased with his drone and we have been enjoying the videos it has captured- really amazing. I will return and upload one as soon as I can get him to cut a video down. He has some very long footage! Do not hesitate to purchase this drone- read the reviews, this is just another one in line with all the other very happy new owners!

title: This is my first real drone and I could not be any happier!
text: I just took this amazing drone out on its maiden voyage!  Wow was I ever impressed! I thought it was probably too windy (6-10 mph) but I really wanted to try this baby out and I am glad I did.  The F11 handled remarkably well, the wind did push it around a little bit, but it was still very easy to navigate.  The app was very smooth and intuitive. title: Excellent flying capability- poor photos/videos (don't buy for photography)
text:
I really wanted to like this drone. This was my first drone with the primary purpose of getting photos and videos perspectives I otherwise would not be able to. It was an exciting prospect.

Flying the drone was surprisingly easy (I had zero experience prior to purchasing it). It is a very maneuverable and steady drone with a lot of very useful features. My primary goal however was to use it as a platform for photography. For this purpose it was quite disappointing. The pictures and videos were marginal, at best- they reminded me of shots captured from a 15 year old Cellphone (poor contrast and white balance, over-sharpened yet not clear, etc.). This was ultimately the deal-breaker for me, and I sent it back as I just could not justify the cost for something I was not going to use for it's intended purpose. It's fun to fly but barely qualifies as a camera platform.

title: More than I bargained for, for sure.... Follow up 12 days later.
text:
Prior to this drone, I used to have Yuneec Q500 4K Typhoon, 3x the price of F11 Pro. I say I "used to" because my CO3 Camera ST10 got busted during last landing (I consider it a flaw in design in the way cables are exposed to stress in case of a hard landing). F11 Pro does not have this issue but the trade off is that video can get a bit shaky in a windy weather. However, at this point, I don't care. My my meager needs, F11 Pro fits the bill. It lasts much longer than my previous drone (Yuneec) which means more air time. On top of it, this "entry" level drone had features that my $850+ Typhoon did not have, namely fly by "wire" so to speak. What I mean by this, set a number of way points, press go, and the drone will execute the path flawlessly. It's great if you want to take a video of an area, for example.

I see plenty of "happy" hours with this drone as it really makes you want to use it rather than worrying about breaking it.

2020-07-16
This is a follow up to my review above. I took 1 star away from my review due to a faulty motor. I had this drone only for 12 days and I had to replace it due to a front right motor failure. Lucky for me, it did not happen up in the air but on the ground when I tried to take off. So, I am not sure if I simply got a lemon or the product itself and workmanship is at fault here.

I have to give high marks to the company for promptly replacing the drone. I got it literally the day after. Thank you, Ruko, for such a great customer support. When criticism is warranted, I will criticize and when praise is required, I will give praise. I took my replacement drone today for its virgin flight. Let's see if this time it does not break after only a few flights.

title: Could be perfect‚Ä¶
text: My friend got a DJI drone and I was really amazed at the technology. I didn‚Äôt want to spend a $1000 so I searched the features and came to this drone. So this drone wowed me during the initial flight. There is a slight learning curve that I had to get past calibrating the compass etc but once it acquires the necessary GPS you‚Äôre ready to fly. This part was what hooked me. Easy to control and the picture is great. You can even set waypoints to have it fly to automatically. The flight time is right at 30mins and will auto return if the battery gets too low. The only major drawback I can see vs other drones is the camera loses signal at around 100 meters. Otherwise this could be a long term keeper. Compared to the DJI mini 2 the distance is roughly 10km. So easily you will reach the max distances of this drone which is assume is the cause for the price difference. BUT the DJI Mini 2 is actually around the same price. So my advice is to go ahead and get the DJI Mini 2 unless you want to just operate within line of sight.

title: It's worth the price
text:
The first drone I bought met it's end in a tree and power line. I guess the interference of the power line wiped out any control I had over it. But before I did that I knew that I wanted another drone that: came with a box/case, had a longer flying time and a camera I could aim.
This drone is soooo much better than the first one I had. It's also a little more than two and a half times more expensive too. As a photog I appreciate the ability to rotate the camera (which isn't a bad little camera for it's size and intended use) to get the angle I need. My first flight was in the back yard under a pecan and crape myrtles. I was able to pretty easily avoid the lawn furniture and branches. It's much easier to control than I expected.
I like the carrying case. It's going to come in handy - I am going to be travelling about the countryside and having the drone protected while bouncing about off road will be nice. It holds the drone, extra battery, controller and extra parts. Plus, there's a zippered compartment in the lid for the instructions and FAA certificate.
What else.....? The camera angle is controllable while flying. That's a huge plus. It's stable and much quieter than the first drone i had.

NOTE: the controller does not accept a "plus" phone like the iPhone 8 plus. it probably wont fit a Note either. Not a deal breaker but it is something that you are going to have to work around. I used a wide rubber band today which worked great, actually. But I'll come up with something that looks a bit more .... well, a bit less "home grown".

title: An excellent beginner drone with big boy features
text:

But I was hesitant to make a large investment until I was sure this would be a hobby I wanted to pursue. I did some research and was astounded at the features on the Ruko F11 at its price-point. title: Issues with Video and Photo Reliability
text:
Rugged, easy to learn and use, smart features, integrates easily with phone. However, there are significant camera limitations. While it advertises a 4K UHD camera, the video on the F11 Pro is 2.7K, and the photos are the same resolution as the video (video and photos are 2976x1680). This means 5 megapixel photos, rather than the advertised 8 megapixel photos if true 4K photos. The video and photos are a fisheye, as would be expected with the 120 degree view. Video can be unstable, since there is no camera stabalization.

Calibration is easy and has been reliable. Hovers very steadily once calibrated. Return to Home feature very accurate. Certain recommend as a beginner drone as long as the video / photo specs meet your needs. Battery life meets advertised flying time.

--Updating review. Still no 4K photos, and more than once the video failed to save to the SD card. Other times the video file is corrupt. Seems the video / photo reliability of this model is lacking.

title: Amazing until it failed, zero customer service
text:
This is (was) my first drone. Was? Yeah, it‚Äôs smoked and no bringing it back to life. That‚Äôs the bad part. The good? I‚Äôm a first timer, so I have nothing to compare it to, but here goes.

The good: Flight capabilities are amazing. It feels well built. The fold in arms are very stable. The motors are powerful and the battery performance was as advertised. Although the motors are brushless, 4 rotors spinning will make quiet a bit of noise‚Äînot a flaw, just a fact of physics.

The bad:
The software is very limited. The same software is used for 4 different drones and you have to select the correct type each time you choose to fly. I did try to set up way point flying, but I couldn‚Äôt get it to work. Cell coverage is very bad in my area, so that may have been part of the issue. In the settings, you can use beginner settings for the allowable range of the drone. If you turn off beginner settings, you can adjust the range to 1200 meters. Be very careful adjusting that range setting. I think this is one reason for fly aways/lost drones.
The manual is not good. It gives you the basics, but you need to find another source to understand the details of things like headless mode and what happens if you turn off GPS. It‚Äôs recommended that beginners fly with support of an experienced operator‚Äîthat‚Äôs a good idea. Definitely want to take time to work through and learn all controls.
The camera is ok, but not great. No stabilization, but that costs more.

The end: Zero customer service. You buy it, you fly it, you break it, maybe you can fix it, maybe you can‚Äôt. I had a motor fail, I attempted to contact customer service via email and have never received a reply. I purchased a replacement rotor assembly, installed it, ended up smoking the electronics, now I have a drone paper weight.

Buyer beware‚Äîdespite the impressive performance, if/when it fails, your money is gone.

text: I bought this drone after reading all the favorable reviews.  I felt like giving it a chance since I had Amazon Prime and could return it if something wasn't right. I receive my new drone and inspected it and found that it was brand new.  I charged the batteries and the remote control unit for a couple of days.  We have been having bad weather with rain and wind for the past two weeks so I decided against test flying it.  Today after connecting the drone to to the app on my iPhone and calibrating the compass and syncing to the GPS I flew it for the first time.  It flew flawless and took outstanding pictures and movie clips.  It cost around $300, but it's well worth it.  I flew it in my backyard for about 25 minutes on one battery.  The controls was great even on my iPhone.  I recommend this drone to anyone whether you are a beginner or a professional.  Start with this one until you are comfortable paying thousands of dollars only to crash an expensive drone.  I've flown both and all sorts and sizes and this one is right up there with the pros.  Don't be frightened over the lack of propeller guards, because this baby is so easy to control you won't need or miss them.  Just buy it you won't be disappointed.

title: Well made feature packed drone
text:
The Roku F11-Pro GPS is my first drone and I could not be more pleased with the product. Although the quick start guide tells you everything you need to know to start flying, I strongly recommend that you read the included manual to better understand all the features of the drone.

Following the flight preparation procedure in the quick start guide, I easily paired the controller with the drone. The Wi-Fi signal from the drone was strong and my phone quickly connected. The calibration process for the drone's compass was straight forward and linking with a GPS signal fairly quick.

Both the drone and controller are well made. The drone is good size and unfolds to a size of 10 x 8.5 inches from motor center to motor center (16 √ó 18 inches from the tips of the propellers). The battery life is very good and will probably come close to the 30 minutes advertised. The drone comes with two batteries, so flight time shouldn't be an issue. The drone comes with extra propellers and screws, charging cable, controller, padded carrying case, and instruction manual. You can also add a 32 GB micro SD card (not included) to the drone to store photos and videos.

The controller has a built in rechargeable battery that outlasts the drone batteries. It has handles that unfold from the bottom of the controller, a spring loaded clasp that folds out from the center of the controller to firmly hold your cell phone, and a dual antenna that also folds out from the body of the controller. The controller is packed with features to fly the drone and control the camera. The 4k camera takes great photos and videos that are transmitted to your phone by the drone's Wi-Fi. With the SJ-GPS Pro App, you can view live video from the drone and control many of the drone's functions. The App is reasonably easy to use and intuitive.

After flight preparation, take off can be accomplished by pushing the left joy stick forward to rev up the motors and launch the drone vertically. You can also press the land/takeoff button on the upper right face of the controller. Two joy sticks are used to control the drone's altitude and direction. Landing can be accomplished in three ways: manually using the joy sticks, pressing the home landing button if you have a good GPS signal, or by pressing the land/takeoff button.

I am still learning how to use all the features this drone includes, such as the follow me mode, way point flight, and point of interest flight.

title: Loses signal only 200ft away, remote antennas empty!!
text: I was very excited to order this, but Amazon has really been letting me down with the expensive products I've been purchasing.  This drone was complicated to setup, but gets easier once you figure out the correct app to download by scanning the QR barcodes on the box.  One of the covers on the remote control antennae is missing, but that's okay because BOTH antennae are empty.  They are totally fake.  That explains why I couldn't get it to fly further than about 200ft before flying back toward me at warp speed.  I am just amazed that this item is listed as #7 in Amazon's RC Quad Copter category.  This is advertised as being for adults, so I expect it to live up to expectation.  It is advertised to have a maximum of 4000feet flight distance.  I understand it says "maximum", but general rule of thumb is you should get 2/3 of what is advertised otherwise the company making the claims is falsely advertising.  I am so upset, that if I were using the words to describe how I really feel about this item, this review wouldn't get published.  I'm beginning to rethink doing business on Amazon entirely with the disappointing streak I've had with the products they allow to be sold, and I don't think my expectations are unrealistic although I realize this has high reviews. title: Better than I hoped for
text: Just want to start by saying I am not giving this 5 stars because I think it is the best drone on the market. I am giving it 5 stars because I believe that at this price point this is about as much as you can ask for. Many features you would find in a much more expensive drone but at a price you can justify for your first learn to fly drone. Took me five mins to get it operational and the drone took right off and held position. Your not going to get image stabilization or 4k video but you will get a crisp image and decent 2.7K video. I wouldn't buy this if making money from drone photography was my thing but if you want to experience what it's like to fly a drone and maybe learn to fly so you can make money then this is a great start. Had my 9 and 10 yo children flying it with very little instruction and no crashes. GPS feature works great and return to home is perfect if you're worried about crash landings. Many more features I didn't mention and some I haven't played with yet but wouldn't hesitate to recommend this drone to any beginner enthusiasts.

title: This is the Drone to purchase  not the Drone .It was me trying to get my wings on my First Flight.
text:
[[VIDEOID:95ad9014d2b1772d9b8b09aabf1fded4]] WOW...This is one amazing drones to purchase.
Let me first .start by saying the first drone I had by the time I had calibrated the compass and the Gyro the battery was half dead. I sent it right back immediately.
I was very discouraged but when I saw the Ruko F11 and the reviews that it received I quickly ordered it and to my surprise it has been a pleasure from the moment I open the box to the few minutes it took to get it up and running I was flying.
I just can‚Äôt say enough good things about this Ruko Drone SJRC F11.
Forget the price this is a steal everything from setting it up the software and I use an Apple phone to the flying smoothness of a Percision instrument.
The reason I mentioned an Apple phone is because I had read that the android system needed some work and upgrades so be aware.
Now let‚Äôs get to the fun part I had this bad boy up and running within five minutes and let me tell you it was smooth sailing no matter what I did or how I did it and I am not a professional it was seamless.
The battery life estate it is correct I was amazed after getting it up in the air and really flying it far away and Highup the battery stayed with me for a good 30 minutes and that to me is amazing.
Controlling in the drone was to my amazement a real pleasure smooth accurate and consistent.
The other thing that impressed me was the software and the features that it offers with the free software integration.
Enclosing may I add a very dear friend of mine had purchased a drone four times the price of this drone and he was blown away.
This is a no brainer.... Order it set it up and have the fun of your life it will do so many things you will not believe it‚Äôs performance I highly rated ....Excellent!
Allan W. Gackstetter. United States Air Force

title: Totally worth the money!
text: This was the first serious drone I bought after flying some little toys.  I LOVE my F11 Pro!  Very easy to fly.  The app is very intuitive and makes it really easy to get everything set up properly.  This drone will return to the takeoff point if it flies out of transmitter range, or if the battery gets too low.  I have tested both of these features and they work great.  A couple times I forgot to check my battery level and suddenly my F11 Pro flew back to me all on it's own!  Because the F11 Pro is heavier than many other drones in this price range, it handles wind better than anything else I fly.  I can fly my F11 Pro on days I couldn't fly anything else.  Flight time on a battery is amazing!  GPS stabilization works beautifully.  If I am headed for trouble, I let go of both sticks and my F11 Pro just hovers in place until I decide what I want to do.  This is a great drone for beginners and intermediates.  In the rural area where I live, I can fly it out to around 250M.  I highly recommend this tough, easy-to-fly drone.

title: Very impressed with this drone!
text:
06/29/2021 I just got this yesterday and have only flown it for a couple hours total so far so this is a first impressions review. I will come back later to update after time has passed and many more hours of flight.

Pros: Follow the instructions and it is easy to calibrate. Once calibrated, it is super easy to fly, as it hovers in place if you let go of the controller sticks. I did find that it is pretty sensitive to movement on the sticks and it will take some time to get used to moving them slowly for a smoother video.
Good video and photo quality. I have added a still with this review to give an example of the photo quality.
The flight time is pretty good! I haven't gotten a whole 30 minutes out of it so far since there has been some pretty stiff breezes while flying over the last 2 days, between 4 and 9 mph (according to my weather station). It handled it very well, though I wouldn't want to fly in anything over that. That's just me.
It connected to satellites, the controller and the android tablet quickly with no problem and stayed connected while I was flying. I only pushed it out to 70 meters so far at 30 meters height so it wasn't a true test.
I tried out the Point of Interest feature, which works great! I also found the return home feature to be very useful. It came close enough to the pad I launched it from to satisfy me, being that there was some wind each time. When it was only blowing a couple mph, it landed within 6 inches of the spot it took off from. The furthest it landed was 3 meters away.

It appears to be well built, solid.

There are only a few things I think could have been better at this price point
The fish eye look when the camera is tilted down - but it does straighten out when the camera is horizontal so I can't complain about that too much.

There could be something to make it more clear which is front and rear when it is flying near enough to see it clearly with the eyes. As long as you're using FPV, that's not bad either.

The only other thing I think could have improved is having a sound when it shuts down as well as the musical sound when it starts up. Another small thing that sure isn't a deal breaker.

title: An awesome drone for beginners!
text: The Ruko F11 Pro is an awesome drone for beginners and enthusiasts. The controls are straightforward and easy to learn. In flight, the drone is highly maneuverable and lots of fun! title: Compact, intuitive and fun! Great drone for beginner through intermediate!
text:
I just received my Ruko F11 Pro Drone from Amazon. I am amazed at how compact and portable it is. I am a beginner drone flyer, but I have watched the instruction video (which wasn‚Äôt too bad), but then I watched Captain Drone‚Äôs review along with another reviewer on YouTube. Both showed off the capabilities of the F11 Pro and really went into details about the operation of the drone.

I love how you can set up a beginners ‚Äúwall‚Äù, where it won‚Äôt go beyond 30 meters away or above you. It is very useful for learning to fly without the ‚Äúheadless‚Äù mode.

One thing that I liked was the quick reference card they provided. The instruction manual is very helpful, but the quick reference card was something that I could have handy while I was flying.

I am very impressed with this drone. I had a Potensic T25, but the battery life was too short, so I purchased the F11. I had 25 minutes of flight my first time out (right out of the box), and there were only three of four charging lights on when I started. I think I will get 30 minutes from a fully charged battery.

The case that it comes in is also perfect, however the drone folds up so nicely that you could drop it in a backpack and not need the case at all. The drone seems very sturdy and I think is made to be able to take a beating.

If I had to complain about anything (so far), it would be that when you mount the phone onto the controller, the side of the phone somewhat blocks access to the buttons that take photos and video. Other than that, I think you will really enjoy this drone!

title: F11 the drone for the new pilots
text:
I took a long time to write a review for the ruko f11 for many reasons. Most importantly is the fact I crashed mine the first day. Ya... I know, it was a stupid crash too of my own poor choice. But the things I expierenced after fixing my drone could of been result of my actions. So I will review what your getting from ruko.

The f11 is a great drone for its price range. It's a great drone for adults to learn with. The f11 also can produce in the field in most ways ruko claims. The package ruko offers however is a matter of POV. This one offers the f11 4k model with spare battery and case.

The f11 is not of ruko but of sjrc. Ruko is also not the only provider of f11 types. Sjrc offers its versions of the f11 as well. Ruko deserves credit and a bit of support for a more recent app released for the f11. If ruko decides to make the app work for only thier named drones, would be tragic and noted. But as far as I know has not come to pass.

Offered in this package is 2 battery. That's not bad, I've seen deals over 300 that only offer 1 from other vendors. Ive also seen packages from vendors under 250 that offer 3 batteries.

It should be noted you are offered a free 3rd battery for giving a positive review. I cannot say I appreciate these offers. It's also why I gave a 4 star review.

title: Buy this!!!!
text:
If you're a newbie this is totally worth it. I've never had a drone and have never flown one. Bought this because of the youtube reviews and reviews on Amazon.

It comes with a spare battery and also another set of propellers. I bought another battery and another set of propellers just in case.

I crashed it into a tree already. Scuffed it up but nothing broken. It was my fault. Initially with the app it is in Beginner Mode. It limits you as to how far, how high it will go/fly. I wanted to go further and higher and somehow messed that up. It tore off and went sideways into a tree. Day 2. I took it off of Beginner mode and adjusted hot far and how high it will go. No problems. Went 341 meters away and 32meters high. No problems and very fun. I like the fly home feature. I can land it myself but it's cool to press a button and here she comes. LOL.

It's very easy to learn on. The app is easy to understand and also has a Quick Start guide in the app which is useful.

The app also logs some stats on your flight. Video is good and it saves to my phone also.

Can't go wrong with this as your first drone. Skip the cheap ones..this one is worth it.

title: Fun little drone!
text:
I had wanted a drone for a while. I didn‚Äôt want a toy, but at the same time didn‚Äôt want to spend hundreds of dollars to buy a ‚Äúreal‚Äù drone. I read several reviews raving about the quality of F11 Pro, but was a bit skeptical. Then Amazon offered the drone as one of their lightning deals. I decided to take the risk and I‚Äôm glad I did.

Flying the drone is relatively easy (I‚Äôm still getting the hang of trying to navigate with the added dimension of up & down). In addition to the instruction manual, there is a quick start guide on the box as well as a handy dandy sheet with instructions on how to begin your first flight. Within a few minutes, I was in the air. Unfortunately a few minutes later I crashed into the side of our porch, but that was due to my piloting prowess, or rather lack thereof, and not the drone. I was worried I might have totaled it, but other than a bit of dirt from hitting the ground everything seemed fine, so I‚Äôm guessing it must be pretty durable.

One of the main criticisms I‚Äôve seen in reviews is the camera quality. I have yet to try filming anything so I can‚Äôt comment on that, but the camera stream on my phone using their app seemed pretty good.

There are several other features (such as the GPS system) which I haven‚Äôt fully explored yet, but even without them I think the F11 is pretty amazing. While it might not be suitable for young children, it makes a great beginner drone if you‚Äôre looking to have some fun without having to spend an arm & a leg.

title: Out of the Box
text: Took me a few minutes to get through all the set up items mostly because I didn't put my phone on the controller 1st. But once I got the calibration set up down and the GPS connected and all the lights were where they were supposed to be. I pulled the controls to the start blades and with a buzzing mini roar they sprang to life and with a push of the L level up she climbed into a stable hover! I was surprised to see the image of myself in the camera. I went through forward and back, up and down, 360 L and R then into a low hover and with the stick back the drone approaches the earth hesitates and slowly lowers itself to the ground and slows the blades!  It helps that I am a Flight Instructor and am used to delicate handling of the controls, but I had the feeling that were I complete newly the result would be the same.  When My wife got home we took it out back this time and took it up a few hundred feet and test the range a little(line of sight only) and brought it back home. Haven't tried all the other modes it's capable of (follow, circle, GPS path etc) but that will have to wait til tomorrow.  In all I am pleased with how it has performed and can't wait to test it out on some of the great places my wife and I like to check out on our motorcycles rides.  Bravo F11

title: This drone is fairly priced since the drone quality is that of a 1,000$ drone.
text:
So far I have enjoyed the flying of the drone every time I launch it I have a smile on my face. It‚Äôs easy to fly easy to set up easy to maneuver flight is steady hovers very accurate due to the awesome gps signal. I have had it as high as about 300meters and the controls are swift to respond.

The camera is excellent as well it takes snap shots from the controller as well as video. The only dislike about the controller is my iPhone 11 barely fits in the holder. Also the camera can be adjusted from the controller 90 degrees which makes spying on anyone pretty easy... üòè

The application that operates the settings of the drone is simple to learn and easy to understand what your adjusting. The directions from the manual are easy to understand if you have flown a drone of pretty much any size. Other wise their is a small learning curve to understanding what your doing when your setting up to fly. But once you get your first flight in you‚Äôll be set.

The speed of the drone is nice not as fast as some but the weight of the drone has a lot to do with that. Up to this point I had only flown smaller drones like the dji ski rider which is about 1/6th the size of the F11 but all in all it‚Äôs quick.

The distance from which you can fly away from the controller is excellent. I was surprised at how far I could go before I was shown on the screen I had weak receiver signal.

It comes with an extra battery which none of the other drones I looked at buying had you had to buy them extra for around 50$US. That was a huge influence seeing as with 2 batteries you can fly up to an hour. The batteries are also excellent they last as long as stated in the description of the item. Also the case is very nice everything has its slot even the extra battery and spare parts. The case is foam lined for protection and zips up tight so nothing flops around.

The follow me setting works well and way point setting too. I have just tried these out I haven‚Äôt used them for any specific reason.

I have no dislikes really the drone is awesome easy to fly easy for beginners to learn. And has awesome distance and altitude. I love it if your in the market for a drone you won‚Äôt be disappointed with the Ruko F11 Pro or the Ruko F11 since the only difference between the two is the camera is 4K on the pro and I believe 1080p on the standard F11. All in all I‚Äôm very happy and satisfied with the product and the price for what you get is about the best for what you get.

title: I‚Äôm a total novice & this worked great for me. Buy it.
text: [[VIDEOID:d49ffea7a7bf53363d3efc3dc1a25177]] I‚Äôm a total newbie when it comes to drones and so is my 20 year old son. 10 years ago my son lost a $60 toy drone when he flew it into a tall tree on its first flight because the technology was immature and unstable back then and he couldn‚Äôt control it. I felt really bad for him but there was nothing we could do. Fast forward to 2020. I bought this drone to get both of us back into the hobby and to correct the mistakes of the past. The video I‚Äôve attached to this review is from our very FIRST flight with this drone! We were able to takeoff and land effortlessly and the controls were very intuitive. The camera takes high quality video and was easy to use. Of course, my son is a total geek and was able to figure out the drone and remote control without even reading the instructions so that was a big help. But there‚Äôs no reason you can‚Äôt do the same if you follow the instructions and take your time. We also watched a couple of YouTube videos that demonstrated how to configure and fly this exact same drone so that was a big help. Some things that were described in the instructions weren‚Äôt clear and the YouTube video cleared up the confusion. It‚Äôs funny because I just assumed that this drone would crash and burn on its first flight just like what happened ten years ago but the exact opposite happened. Both of our initial flights were an astounding success and my son had a great time flying this thing. In fact I had to plead with him for the remote control so that I could get some flying time. Each of the two batteries lasted about 22 minutes which was plenty of flight time for us. Needless to say, we are both hooked and can‚Äôt wait for our next flight. This drone was a lot more stable and controllable than I expected. With the GPS feature enabled It almost seemed to have a mind of its own when it comes to takeoff and landing. And the return to home button worked like a charm. What a difference ten years makes. Overall I am very pleased with the high quality and performance of this drone and I would recommend it to any beginner. If you‚Äôre on the fence and, like me, can‚Äôt decide whether $300 is worth it, let me tell you that it is worth every penny. Just buy it, and you can thank me later.

title: Wait what? Read my honest review...
text:
I don't know where to start really. This drone is loud...at least compared to my DJI Mini 2. I wasn't expecting a DJI out of a Roku certainly. However with all the glowing reviews for this drone surprised me once I got it and took it out for a demo.

The range is not very good. It's not even decent. You can go just about a mile out, but only if unobstructed. On fact, once I started to get about 400 ft out, controls were in and out. I did manage to get out about 600 ft befor the drone decided it was time to RTH.

I think video quality was ok for a couple hundred ft, but wasn't 4k by any stretch. I believe it is "upscaled" 720p.

This drone also does the toilet bowl thing. Very strange thing to witness.

The remote is super basic and feels cheap. The "antennas" aren't. The actual antenna is inside the control box.

The app is so vague that one actually has to read the directions to figure out what some of the hieroglyphics mean. There are a couple of doodads on the back of the remote that do not serve a purpose.

Battery life was a dismal 16 minutes on one fully charged battery and 18 on the other fully charged battery.

But wait, there's more.

Just kidding. You get what you pay for....or in this case, you're paying about 300 bucks for a nice 115 dollar drone that probably costs 40 dollars to make in China.

Pros: Very easy to fly

Phone app was easy to use

Cons: Takes forever to charge batteries when using computer as charging source, should have included a wall charger.

I recommend purchasing a wall charger, seller recommends a max 15 watt charger with 5V/3A for charging and also need a sun shield for phone when flying outdoors, both available on Amazon. For the wall charger I got one with two usb ports each providing 5V/2.4 amps which charges the batteries in just a few hours.; the one I got is also a multistage charger meaning I can leave the batteries connected overnight without fear of overcharging, when the batteries are fully charged the charger automatically goes into a maintenance mode. Read the Sun shield descriptions as many are just cardboard with cloth covering, not substantial enough to last.
Charger: USB Charger, Anker Elite Dual Port 24W Wall Charger, PowerPort 2 with PowerIQ
Sun Shield: HeiyRC 5.5 inch Drone Remote Control Sun Shade Hood

Highly recommend for anyone interested in drone flying.

text:
I just received this drone and have only flown it for about 20 minutes so I'll update this review if necessary later.
Out of the box this drone felt well made and good quality. Came with nice storage case, extra battery, extra blades.
After learning the start up process I left the drone in beginner mode and had no trouble at all flying this drone around a large field. I am not a drone expert and felt this drone was perfect for me both for price and other reviewers saying about it. I do have an issue with camera not moving but I haven't gone through troubleshooting tips on that yet and I'm sure it is a simple issue as described in documentation. Camera image is very good, I'd say excellent. Only issue is if there is any wind and you don't control drone well enough the image will be a bit shaky but not bad. You won't be using the footage in a feature film anyway so it is very good for this price. The drone was very responsive, fast, and easy to control and maneuver. I'd recommend this drone for anyone looking to get into the hobby and want to start with a drone that is lower cost, easy to fly, and takes great images.

title: This is really a great drone for beginners like me
text:
This is my first drone. Never had one before and I honestly don't know a lot about them.
I found this easy to use, the instructions are pretty clear cut and even the video presents the information well (even if the English is a little stilted).
The return to home feature is really cool as well. It took me a few flights to start getting the hang of it and I didn't realize at first that the memory card goes in 'upside down' - so if it's sticking out at all, flip it over in relation to the 'top' of the drone and it will go all the way in.
I haven't tried it with any of the clip on VR 'googles' yet, but I will eventually to see how that does. I also appreciate the altitude setting for return flight as there are a lot of trees in my area.
Overall I'm very happy with this purchase.

title: Built and Flys like a more expensive drone!
text:
[[VIDEOID:e7c2a8b824aaf3bdb48daa92df108ac6]] Got this drone about a week ago and have put in about 10 hours so far in the hot Texas sun. I have flown other more expensive drones and I was very suspect as to how this drone would be. Needless to say I WAS NOT disappointed!

FEATURES YOU WILL LOVE
I did extensive research and need a drone to inspect my roof with the recent electrical storms that we have been having. My major requirements were great quality FPV camera, well built and long flight time. This drone remarkably exceeds all that and more. Not only does thie F11 Pro fly like a champ (even in moderate wind), it has amazing features like a more expensive drone. I have used the automatic takeoff and landing which is accurate to roughly 1 ft or less. The safety features for beginners, like a safety range and auto return are excellent. In fact, my wife didn't want to fly it until I showed her how well those safety features worked. One of the things that I absolutely love on this drone is the ability to toggle the reaction time for the flight controls. Located as a roller switch at the top left, I can toggle whether I want the F11 Pro to respond quickly or have a software response for my wife and 3 year old nephew. It has all the other features like more expensive drones like follow me, waypoint navigation and orbit.

BUILD QUALITY
This drone is so well built! It seems its made very sturdy plastic but not brittle. I thought since this was a decent priced drone it was meant for more seasoned pilots that wont knock it around. Well I realized quickly that this thing is super durable. Since the F11 Pro allows you to learn really quickly with its safety features, I didn't have MAJOR crashes, but I have ran it into a few things (Fence, Chairs, Wall) trying to learn how to land. Just when it thought I completely destroyed the props, to my surprise they were just fine. AND the F11 pro come with replacement props so it even better. Its super quiet and handles great at high altitude or in ground effect.

CAMERA
One of the requirements was a 4K camera, good luck trying to find a drone in this price range with an articulating camera. All the other drones I researched showed the FPV video quality like 720p or worse. Even the 1080p drones sometimes only recorded 1080p and wasn't necessarily broadcasting in that resolution. This drones video quality is outstanding (see the attached video), the pictures look incredible. I was able to get great pictures for my roof inspection. I have not had the video feed drop out or even begin to lose connection. I cant wait to try test out its range in an open field eventually.

BUY THIS DRONE... you will not be disappointed, I'm getting obsessed! Happy flying!

title: Great product, great drone, truly worth it‚Äôs money!
text:
[[VIDEOID:c77900b29519fc7724889c946178ad52]] Throughout the many years, I have had many remote control helicopters and have never been satisfied with any of them.

So it came up time again for another helicopter and I came across the Roku F11.

I ordered it and after ordering it I was initially hesitant as I was not certain it was really going to be the helicopter that it is.

I read so many different stories good and bad about so many different helicopters I figured the deal I got was a good deal and I decided to jump in headfirst and purchased it.

My initial response was kind of dismay. I ordered the F11 pro.

My initial response was well I just don‚Äôt get this. It folds up nice and small. It came with two batteries a little screwdriver and a couple sets of helicopter blades and the helicopter and the remote control.

Initially I charge the batteries and was very happy the next day when I woke up and they both were green good to go.

I had tried playing with the helicopter at home. But I was not ready to turn it on and take it out for a flight until I was certain I was in a place where I knew I would not ruin it on my first flight

I had emailed the company back-and-forth a couple times about questions about the helicopter. The company was very forthcoming and responsive to my stupid questions.

Of course the company never referred to my questions as being stupid.

So here I am at a campground in north eastern Pennsylvania. They have a part of the campground where hot air balloons take off daily. So we thought that would be a great place to try out the helicopter.

So our first day was a little bit of a learning curve. I have had other helicopters but none of them ever were successful and we‚Äôre not GPS or any quality whatsoever.

I watch the video on how you should use your new drone for the first time. It listed the five things you should do before you‚Äôre confident enough to take your drone out.

So we followed his steps and it was definitely worth practicing our landings hovering and basic Fleitmann ship skills.

One of our first big things we were the happiest with was bringing up the helicopter to 75 feet and turning on the camera and spinning around in a circle.

We had some great photographs that we took over the next couple days.

We had one near miss as I accidentally turned off the GPS and the helicopter went flying into the woods. It‚Äôs survived and work just as well afterwards.

We practice the next couple days taking off and landing taking photographs and adjusting the camera and moving around the camera mount and the angle.

At this point we are very comfortable with the hovering going up and the items that really are needed in basic flight.

At this point we had learned to bring a couple chairs with us and sit in the field with an obstructed view. On our second day my wife decided she could fly it as well. I was so happy that she got to try it and enjoyed flying it. It kind of made it even more fun for me watching her fly at as opposed to me concentrating on just flying.

Another couple days went by and we learned more and more skills. We purchased one of the instant helicopter pads and it worked wonderful. My wife was able to take off at a pretty high speed and come down and land pretty close to the helicopter pad.

After our first day of flight we brought on the batteries and plug them in to charge. But unfortunately we did not bring our charging cables with us.

So we went home and got our tables and were able to charge the batteries for the next day.

We really had a lot more fun on the next day and each day forward.

So I truly think it is a great helicopter and has a lot of high-end benefits.

I was originally surprised by the compressed Styrofoam carrying case. But I have learned to like that as well. It holds all of the items perfectly.

They came with the two batteries and now we have two cables we will keep in the case along with a charger.

On my complaint list it would have to be the directions were printed on a microscopic font. But I am older than your average teenager who can read better.

So we took photographs of the directions and I was able to see them with my iPad Pro. It was also easier to see him when they are inverted in color.

We‚Äôve attached some of the photographs. The videos came out in great quality and the photographs came out and great quality. Taking photographs and sharing them was quite easy.

The consul display was easy to follow and once we figure that out we were doing pretty good. We need to complete lesson number three to become more proficient at flying takeoff and landing.

All in all we give it thumbs up. Very easy to learn. I can‚Äôt wait to explore some more of the Pennsylvania woods.

It‚Äôll take some time before I reach the comfort level where I feel comfortable flying around in my neighborhood.

So thumbs up. Great value and great price great quality.

title: What a Thrill Right Out of The Box! You Will Feel Like A Pro! It's Made To Fly and Have Fun!
text:
[[VIDEOID:3d06e80d130f86cf3b86663be6d4e8fc]] There are few products or services that get it right. This is one of them. Years ago I bought a drone and it was a small but nicer one. It was hard to fly, hard to control and ended up broken, then repaired but never used again. It was just not fun. Fast forward to today and the Ruko company got it right.

I researched for months about what to buy, what would be good for me as a beginner, but as I became more experienced would do what I would want it to do. Well this Ruko drone does all that.

When you open the box for the first time, it feels like you are opening something of a much higher priced item. The packaging is sleek and well thought out. The feeling is of an experience, not just opening a product. Once inside, the drone and its accessories are packages well inside a wonderful foam lined case. Again, you realize that much thought went into every little detail.

I followed the instruction for charging the batteries, reviewed the flight instruction as well as the app instructions. Please take your time to review everything, as with me, it was all new.

My Son and I took it outside to take our first flight. I was very nervous, like I said the last time I flew a drone, it was a horrifying experience. We did the initial setup and turned on the motors and WOW!!! It fly to a preset height and just stayed there. No all over the map. Just stayed at the height it was set at. We began to slowly take it through its paces and it did everything it promised it would and more. Again WOW, it was such a pleasure to fly and feel in control.

We had it set to beginners mode in the app, we downloaded from the andriod store, as we used an old Moto g6. I could not believe how easy and how much control you have over this great Ruko drone. Again, it has so many features to help you maintain control and if something goes wrong, you hit the "return home" button and sure enough, it returns back to you. We tried it and in our case, it landed within 1 foot of where it took off from.

For me, I truly am impressed with the quality and feel of this drone. Once you feel more comfortable with the drone, you can switch out of beginners mode and do many other things on your own control. This drone made be feel like a kid again, but also because of the thought that was put into the complete experience of the Ruko drone, I felt like a true polit. I could have fun as well as know that much thought had gone into making it fun, but safe and if an issue would to come about, that it would return to me and not just be lost forever.

You do have to register it with the FAA as it is a larger drone, but that took me 5 minutes and I had my number to put on the drone.

I have posted a video of our first flight. Again, for once, I feel like I got a product that not only was true to its statements, but went above that and I felt that I had received much more then what I paid for. In todays world, that is normally no the case.

Well Done Ruko, Well Done.

Thanks for giving my Son and I a great experience and memories of a good time.

Glenn

title: Deciding between an F11 Pro and a F11 GIM?
text:
This was the first drone I've ever purchased. Let me start off by saying it was very easy to learn how to use it. You get great instructions with this along with an extra battery, controller, and sturdy carrying case. It only took me about 10 minutes to get used to the features of this drone. When using the app on your phone along with the remote, media is also stored on your mobile device (although, the quality isn't as good as what comes off of the memory card). One downside for me was the fact that this drone only accepts a 32GB memory card. If you're anything like me, you've probably been comparing this drone with the newer F11 GIM. Let me help you out here. As my focus for this purchase was to take great pictures and video, I found the capabilities in that area to be just satisfactory. The F11 Pro takes decent looking video and good images. It does have a bit of the "fisheye" going on. That being said, I ended up returning this drone and decided to go for the F11 GIM. I will say, getting used to the flight operation of the GIM took me a little bit longer to get used to. For example, on the F11 Pro, you could rotate the left joy stick and the drone would turn (in place). On the Gim, doing the same action makes the drone turn but it covers a wider area, so you have to pay attention if you're operating it with objects nearby. I wish the GIM shared the precision of movement that the F11 Pro has. The being said, the pictures and video taken on the GIM had me saying "wow" when I saw them on my computer. The colors seems to look better as well. The image and video quality is much better on the GIM. I've added two photos, one from the PRO and one from the GIM. These were pulled from my phone but you can see some differences (1st is from the PRO, 2nd is from the GIM)

Bottom Line: If your on the market for a great done that gives you a lot of value, with precise controls and is fun to fly, get the F11 Pro. If you're looking for a drone that will take amazing images and video, get the F11 GIM. I hope that helps!

I found better tutorials via searching and went with those as opposed to the Ruko vid. The software has to be reset to connect to the correct drone every time - not a deal breaker but an annoyance.

title: Great beginning drone that met my expectations and more.
text: The packaging for the F11 Pro drone is very good. The foam insert with cutouts is a great way to store the drone and accessories and offers above average protection to the drone and accessories. The controller is a bit small at first but with practice I found it to be adequate for my needs. I do wish there were a way to use a table rather than a phone for flight only because the larger picture would be more plausible. Other manufacturers provide an aluminum frame that holds the controller and a tablet. Ruko does not (please look at offering such a frame). Connecting the phone to the drone is simple and quick. The app is easy enough to follow. The drone starts quickly (I recommend following the startup procedure in the app - it is easier to follow than the paper guides). Flying the drone is not difficult although I left it in beginner mode and did not attempt difficult procedures. Did I crash? Absolutely. When landing I tried coasting near the ground and the legs caught the grass and flipped the drone. No damage done, just some mud on the top and side of the drone. I definitely need more practice and expect my skills to improve with each outing. All of this to say flying the drone is fun and enjoyable; the drone meets my expectations; the quality of the drone is good; and the experience overall exciting and pleasing.

title: Take your time and watch the instructional video and you will really enjoy this drone.
text:
I didn't see any instruction on turning off your cellular connection, but I did have to do this to make the video work. Once I did that, this thing is great.

Once you lift the restrictions (after you get used to flying it) this thing is fairly fast and the range is really good. Once you loose video, you can press the return to home button and then cancel once the video reconnects. The video range depends somewhat on your phone for sure.

The images were much better than I expected and I hear they are better if you use a card, which I haven't installed yet. Took some nice pics of the snowy neighborhood. The video worked well too.

I flew it well under 30 degrees with no problem, but 12 degrees F was too cold. It was unstable and it complained about the battery being low prematurely. To be fair, this is well under the operating range and ice was starting to form on the body and blades.

Is this as good as a DJI in the same price range? (I don't think there is a DJI in this range.) I would put it up against a DJI mini fairly well, although the video range and full gimble goes to DJI (it might have other categories as well). The F11 definitely was quicker than the mini and is heavier, so might not be as vulnerable to the wind.
If this is in your price range I don't think you will be disappointed. I definitely don't regret this purchase.

title: Value-packed, Solidly-built, Great for Beginners, Advanced enough to be FUN!
text:
[[VIDEOID:ae89eb0f01731809ae4274c025172a09]] As a first-time drone flyer, I wanted more than "toy-class" but didn't want to be intimidated by a steep learning curve. The F11 Pro is sturdy, easy to learn, robust and has many advanced features you usually find on $1k-plus models. Downloaded app from the internet installed it on an unused iPhone & I was flying within minutes! The default beginner mode keeps you out of trouble until you get a handle on flight characteristics. Once it's locked onto GPS, it held steady in moderate winds. The "return home" mode works whenever you fly outside of boundaries or when the battery is close to dying (or whenever you want it to come home).

The only weak point might be the lack of two-way camera gimbal to stabilize video footage when maneuvering, but for the most part, video is reasonably good when the drone itself is stable in flight. The camera resolution is a bit weird (somewhere between 2K and 4K), but since most users will probably covert the video footage into a more standard format before editing, that's not a big deal, especially at this price level.

Bottom line: the F11 Pro is nicely-built, the flight software is easy to learn but has enough "high-end" tricks built in to keep you interested, customer service is fast & friendly when you need help, the camera/SD card setup makes footage easy to transfer to computer (it also lets you alternately capture your footage & photos on the cel phone you're using to run the flight control app), and it's robust enough to survive your first few inevitable crashes!

title: Good beginner drone. Fun to use! Pro & Cons
text:
OVERVIEW: First off, this is a beginner drone! Second: if you are brand new to drones, and aren‚Äôt loaded, get a drone like this one as there is a learning curve and risk with drones if you want to push the limits and have some fun with it, which we all want to do. And thirdly: if you are finding the instructions confusing, I would strongly recommend watching a 3rd party YouTuber like captain drone or something.

PROS:
‚Ä¢Fun
‚Ä¢Fast
‚Ä¢Responsive controls
‚Ä¢Lots of fun features for a beginner drone
‚Ä¢Price/quality - it‚Äôs a well made drone, it survived a 30 foot fall after hitting a tree pretty well, the blades were slightly scuffed up
‚Ä¢Prettt good 2k camera

CONS:
‚Ä¢Title is misleading about the battery life. This is something that frustrates me more than anything, if you put 60 minute fly time in your title, that implies that you can stay in the air for roughly 60 minutes right? Well no. You get roughly 60 minutes between the 2 batteries you get. So 25 min/ea is a safe bet if there is low wind and you aren‚Äôt racing it non-stop. This is the thing that dropped my review from a 5 to a 4. I want complete honesty in things like this. It‚Äôs like saying your new electric car can go 800 miles, but they don‚Äôt tell you that that means swapping out your battery half way which they‚Äôve included.
‚Ä¢Range is not the advertised range. I think 4000ft is what is advertised, which is a little less than a mile. This goes no where near that range. Maybe 1000? I‚Äôm not sure.
‚Ä¢Instructions can be a little confusing - again go watch a YouTube video on the drone to make it easy.

CLOSING: fun drone, I‚Äôm in my mid 20s and I‚Äôm having a blast with this. You may be tempted to get yourself a mavic pro 2 or something because that‚Äôs what all the youtubers will say. If you are brand new, don‚Äôt do it!! There is too much risk. And I doubt you are going to insure your drone. Make sure you are going to stay committed to your ‚Äúvideography‚Äù career before you go all out on a high end one.

title: Drone w features
text:
‚ïî ‚ñ† Price Point / Value: 5/5
‚ï† ‚ñ† Build Quality: 5/5
‚ï† ‚ñ† Media Quality: 5/5
‚ï† ‚ñ† Recommendation: 5/5
‚ï† ‚òº Overall: 5/5
‚ï† ‚ñ∫Product Need: Intermediate drone
‚ï† ‚ñ∫Product Pros: HD video/pics, case, 2 large batteries, one button start, auto return, .75mi range GPS, warranty, fast
‚ï† ‚ñ∫Considerations: Will need to connect to phone, no safety guards
‚ï† ‚ñ∫My Review: I have owned a ton of drones from the mini handheld ones to the Mavic and can say this is a great drone buy for the intermediate flyer. It could be for beginners as well, and while the price point is a great value, it might scare some users who spend less and end up not happy with their drone. This is very easy to learn and control with its auto start and return feature, very long battery, latest 4k technology, and GPS with follow me which are all the top features a great drone should have. Each battery lasts about 25 minutes of fly time and there are two batteries included. They charge fast and full in a couple of hours so you could continuously charge through while flying. The drone itself has a brushless motor which is what you would see in top tools for its durability and quality. It has a bunch of advanced features like adjusting camera angle, GPS hold, GPS map points, circle an area, 5gz connection and comes with extra propellers. You do have to connect it to your phone trough their app which gives you the full ability to control and access the extra features, while the joystick remains for the controls. The app is easy to use and navigate through. It fold up as it should and fits a very nice lightweight foam case. The picture and video quality are better than I expected at this price even for 4k. For a good fraction of the top drone price, it definitely gives the Mavic a run for its money. I would definitely recommend this to any level drone user and is a very good value at the price point.

title: Well, so far so bad......
text: First, I've flown other drones (Mavik, mavik mini) that friends and relatives have and decided to try this out.  After watching many videos and seeing positive reviews of the F11 pro i ordered it.  received yesterday and took it out 1st time today.  Sunny day a few clouds slight breeze (3-4 mph).  After running the setup, connecting to WiFi, opening the app everything seemed to be going well.  I began carefully by just doing auto launch and was working fine.  I did minor moves at 20 ft, within a distance of about 50-75 ft.  Was getting used to the controls and the app after about 15 mins.  suddenly clouded up a bit and the wind started to kick up to maybe 5-7 mph.  Decided it was enough for the first flight so I used the return to home to make sure it worked.  I was working fine, seemed to handle the wind fine.  Just as it was coming in to land, about 3 inches from the ground there was a sudden wind gust and the drone tipped a bit to the left and propellers on that side hit the sidewalk and the unit flipped over and landed updside down !!! :(  After picking it up, there was no visible damage except for some cosmetic damage on the propellers that had hit the sidewalk.  Turned everything off and took the unit inside for awhile.  about an hour later the day was back to as before, clouds gone, sunny, slight breeze so I took it back out to check everything.  Bad news.  Everything seemed to initialize (compass, gps, wifi) but the camera would not display anything in FPV.  Also, the camera would not rotate via the controller.  It just stayed in the same place no matter what.  Camera basically dead.  Naturally had to send this back and had to decide whether to get replacement or refund.  Decided to get a replacement, hopefully this was just a one off issue.  Will have to see.  I will update this review on the new unit after it is received.  If I have other issues will just have to get a refund and look at a different drone.

title: EXCELLENT Beginner Drone!
text:
if you've read any of my reviews, you know that I like to wait until the 'new car smell' wears off to write them so I can give a more honest picture of how happy (or unhappy) you will be with this purchase. So, here is my take on the RUKO F11 drone.
I am not a professional user of drones. Far from it-- I am an absolute rookie, so please understand that my perspective is based on a limited set of expectations. When this product came up on a pre-Christmas price drop, I checked the reviews for any pattern of bad juju and, Seeing none, too the plunge. I am VERY happy I did! Here were my factors for selection, all of which have proven to be accurate for this drone:
-Ease of use. Both I and my 10 year old had no trouble learning the basics. The instructions are clear and usable.
-Feature packed. This is a LEGIT drone. I has most of the advanced features you will find on a much pricier unit. I am still learning some of them, but they are all explained clearly, so... start having fun and learn as you go!
-Good camera! This is a 4K camera, so it takes beautiful pics and video.
-Sturdy, with a qualifier. It is well made, but this is a sensitive electronic device designed to be light weight, so don't let the dog play with it.
-Good battery life. It'll stay in the air for a good while. If you are working it hard, you'll kill the battery faster (duh) , but it will stay up pretty close to the stated 30 mins if you are conservative with it. It comes with two batteries (good) but they do take a while to charge back up, so if you need a LOT of hang time you may wish to buy an extra. They charge with a regular old mini USB instead of a dedicated charger, so you can have multiple batteries charging simultaneously. The controller lasts a long time and charger fairly quickly.
-Carrying case is nice. I'd pay extra for the case that comes with this unit (but I'm glad I didn't)
-Comes with parts. Haven't broken anything yet, but it is inevitable. The drone came with a bunch of blades.
-Does well in the wind! Surprisingly, a good breeze is not a problem for this thing!
In sum, So far I have nothing bad to day about this unit. I hope this review helps you with your decision.

title: Ruko F11 Pro Drone with Camera
text:
I am very pleased with the Ruko F11 Pro Drone. I took it out of the box, followed the clear instructions, charged all the batteries, and was ready to test it the next day. My primary purpose for purchasing it was to use it to see things in the 500 acres of trees we farm, particularly the location of beavers that destroy the trees and feral hogs that do extensive damage to the landscape. I've been practicing in a clear area, and I'm almost to the point that I'm ready to move out to various areas of the farm; the condensed instructions are very helpful as I fly the drone. I also appreciate the relatively long battery life (30 minutes) and the crystal clear pictures/videos I get with it. I often say when I buy equipment that it'd be nice if things worked as advertised--this drone does!
What would I change to make it even more useful? I'd add a small light in the center of the back so I'd always be able to see the orientation of drone; I'm going to add reflective tape. Of course, I'd prefer cheaper replacement rotary blades, but cost is comparable with other brands.
I highly recommend the drone; based on my experience to date, I don't think you can go wrong with it!

title: A fun and simple to use drone
text:
It is a fun first drone to have. It is easy to use and has lots of helpful features to make your first flights as smooth and as safe as possible. I live in a mountains region and during my first flight the wind picked up drastically. Enough to overpower the drone preventing it from using its auto home feature. When the power finally died mid flight, we went to look for it using the gps last know location feature. Since the drone died before it touched down, its last know location wasn't close enough to were it landed. Untimely we couldn't find the drone and I reached out to the Ruko support line. They got back to me very quickly and once I sent them the flight logs of the drone that went missing, they were able to send me a replacement. The replacement was definitely an older model (slightly heavier and uses micro usb instead of type-c) but I wouldn't be able to tell while flying it.

Now that I have hard more experience with the drone I can say that it is pretty great! The controls aren't as tight as I would like but they are very intuitive and easy to pick up. Safety features like auto landing and distance limiters work great even under less then ideal circumstances. Just keep an eye on the weather. If you start having issues with either of those safety features, it's likely the result of external factors and you should try to land immediately.

I would definitely recommended this as a fun first recitational drone.

title: Fantastic Customer Support and Great Little Drone
text:
I have always wanted a drone but was tentative in buying one as I thought it would be difficult to learn. I have never used the joy stick controllers in games or anything like that before (I'm old and "old school"). After reading all the great reviews and watching numerous YouTube videos highlighting this RUKO F11 Pro drone, I took the plunge. I had it for 5 months before I even tried to fly it. When I finally did, I was disappointed that the SD card in the drone wasn't capturing photos or videos. I knew the camera was working as the images were being captured in the RUKO PRO APP and on my cell phone. But I wanted to be able to take the SD card and view the images on my larger screen laptop. After changing out 3 different 32 GB FAT32 formatted SD cards, I was at my wits end. Finally, I emailed RUKO customer service with my problem. I fully explained all the steps I had taken up to that point. The friendly (and fast responding) Customer Service team determined that the drone was not communicating with the SD card correctly. They sent me a replacement camera at no charge. It arrived in a matter of days. (I was afraid I would have to wait months seeing as how these things were made in China.)

I can't say enough about the great response I got from RUKO Customer Service. I HIGHLY recommend this drone and this company. I will buy another RUKO drone when I decide to upgrade to a more advanced model.

title: Very good Drone, many variations, and that is part of the problem
text:
By many variations, I am serious that the vendor is selling so many versions of this chassis and software that the Quick Operation Guide (in the lid of the box) lists the use of "SJ GPS PRO_XXXX" instead of the complete manual that states that you use the "RUKO PRO" app. The software differences are extreme! That was the first problem since ALL of the similar units set up and find GPS the same way.

Second, The instructions don't warn you not to use an older Android Version like v8.0 which my ASUS phone that I was going to use uses. They just warn that it won't work unless you have WIFI for 5g (not 2.4g). I struggled for over an hour trying to get the Drone to show video, and stay connected to the Drone. The phone is totally stable on my home WIFI 5g - Not the drone. I would have taken off two stars if I knew better to start with - I take some responsibility for not figuring it out.
Also, the software interface uses different icons to enable the advanced features depending on what 'version' of the Pro app you use. Initially, my phone kept dropping out of connection further exacerbating the issue!

Third, the app uses one icon that looks a lot like the GPS return icon that buries 8 different functions and the manual initially only addresses this as 'More Functions'. I tried for 30 minutes to find the Waypoint flight. It is ONE of these 8 functions!

Fourth, I just noticed that the Take Off button tells the Drone to take off and hover at about 5 ft - well on my slightly inclined driveway ended up more like 8 -10ft. Good thing I didn't assume I could do that indoors, or my ceiling fans would have eaten the Drone!

I am sure I will find out more, but these are my observations in Beginners Mode after 2 hours of struggle. I think after killing two batteries and loading two Apps that I can now set up Waypoints and film a surround view of my home roof (preparing for Solar).

Update: The Drone works great when you know how to find the Waypoints section. Will try now some of the advanced features. We are in a very wooded area, and flight is precarious, so I use even more caution. But if the Gyros and Compass are set properly, the Drone will hover perfectly while you get your act together!

text:
This is my 3rd drone and I'm finally glad I spent a little more money to have something that is easy to learn with. My first drone was a micro drone that was a nightmare to control and the second was similar in size to this Ruko, but it did not hover well, was not easy to control and it would take off if it lost control, which it did once and was only saved from flying off into the deep woods by a tree top pulling the battery back out before it left my property. I brought out for the 2nd time today and got a little brave with it on a mildly windy day and it wasn't too bad down low, but I brought it up a bit too high and got a little nervous as it seemed to be caught in some pretty strong winds up over the tree line. I was able to get it back under control and all was well. I have taken a few pictures so far and one came out pretty nice with my son testing the gesture feature.
