title: Easy to pickup and learn, responsive control, GPS issues
text:
This drone is very easy for a new person to learn, the controls are responsive and in most cases the GPS allows very accurate control of the drone.

For the first couple of months of owning this drone, most flights were without issue. The return home feature for the most part worked to a limit, I normally had to guide it in for the landing as it would try to land around 10 to 20 feet of where the takeoff spot was. Control range with the controller was normally spectacular, however, the phone and video signal, in my area which give is a more crowded area and would have quite a bit of interference was around 40 to 80ft. In an area with very minimal, I could get around 200 to 400 ft and still have video transmission.

The only issue I had, which unfortunately resulted in the loss of the drone, was the return home feature started taking the drone in the slightly wrong direction. After noticing I tried to cancel and manually return but by that point it was outside of the controller's range. Attempted to locate via last known position but was not to be found in that area.

Otherwise, this was an extremely fun one to fly but was disappointed to see it go.

title: Awesome drone!!
text: I own 3 other drones, each one less than $50. They work great and are fun to fly but I wanted one that could do more. The ruko f11 is awesome! Super easy to set up. This model comes with 2-30 minute batteries and extra blades. Batteries come with a factory charge but it's best to fully charge both before you fly. Scan the QR to download the app. The app is very user friendly. The pictures and videos that this drone take are absolutely amazing. It also has GPS and it works flawlessly. I paid about $300 for this drone and it was worth every penny! Learning to fly it was so easy. I have also used a set of VR goggles which were mind blowing to use. I highly recommend this drone.

title: Did lots of research and....
text: WOW! I did a lot of research and although I was prepared to spend a little more on a GPS drone but, for the price ($250), I kept coming back to this one. It has everything I was looking for; foldable, POI, way point flight, return to hone, object tracking, 30 min flight time, 4K and a hell of a lot more. I read some neg reviews about the app, but it works perfect for me (galaxy s9+). Incredibly easy to fly. In fact you just tell it what to do and it does it.  The drones that cost about $1000 more do have a few features that this one lacking. Like obstacle avoidance. But honestly, this is so easy to fly, I don't know why you would need it.  Anyway, do yourself a favor, get the F11 Pro. At this price, I don't think anything else comes close.

title: Very User Friendly
text: This is an awesome quad. This is my first drone and I researched the various drones out there. This F11Pro is mid level experience but also has a beginners mode that is really an awesome feature. First their website is really well put together and Very informative. I would suggest to watch the videos first as I did, really helpful to understand the "tricks" to easy flying. Out of the box, and after I'd charged the battery to full, I was flying in about 20 minutes. Very easy to sync my phone to the controller and app, sync quad to control, and calibrate the GPS. Very easy and the app is really good, functional and easy to use. The controller is well designed and makes flying very east. Flight controls are not overly sensitive but at the same time very responsive. If you let go of controls, quad hovers in place. The RTH function brings it right back home. Highly recommend this quad for adults that are new to this as I am. I'm sure after a few more practice sessions I'll be rocking and rolling.

title: Battery life and camera
text: For this being my second drone just learning. This thing is amazing being able to fly almost and hour with both batteries. The camera is awesome. I got around 400 meters live stream before it stared getting choppy. But I also live in the mountains so idk if that has anything to do with it. Highly recommended for anyone.

Only downside and the reason for 4 stars...the phone holder bracket is made for a very slim phone. Even my iphone11 with a slim silicone case would not stay in and even "jumped out" a few times while test fitting at home. We will likely always have 2 of us, one to fly the other holding our phone, watching & directing. However, if you wanted to use this by yourself, using the phone app with the controller might just prove impossible.

Calibrating the drone is easy, the associated app works great, and the return to home feature has been really helpful as it allows my son to land the drone automatically within a foot or two of the takeoff point. This is a great drone for someone looking for their first GPS controlled non-toy drone but isn't ready to commit a $1000 for the next level up.

title: Awesome drone with great features.
text: I have never flown a drone, or anything remote control for that matter. I was skeptical as to how easy it would be to control and fly while still being enjoyable. I received the drone on Thursday and charged the two drone batteries and the controller battery that evening. I read the instructions and watched a couple of videos on how to fly it. I took it out Friday afternoon to the middle of a field and followed the instructions to get it set up. Within 15 minutes I was up and flying. I kept it in beginner mode as I practiced with the controls and explored several of the amazing auto features as well as taking photos and video. As I was flying at about 15 feet high and about 30 feet away, the drone started coming back toward me and I wasn't controlling it. I looked down at my phone (iPhone 11pro Max) and saw the battery meter on the drone was red. Then drone returned to within 3 feet of where it took off from and landed and shut down. I didn't even realize that I had been flying it for 26 minutes when it returned to me. I took the battery off and put the fresh battery on the drone and turned it on. My phone screen said Ready To Fly, so I started it up and took off again. I did not have to do any setup for the second flight. I took it off of beginner mode and started to explore further. I went up to 120 meters and out to a distance of about 800 meters when I lost connection to the cell phone. The camera was frozen on where it dropped the signal. It was so high and bright outside that I had no idea where it was, only the general direction it was in. I hit the return home button and waited, thinking it must have disappeared and fell. Within a couple minutes I could hear it above me, and I looked up but still couldn't see it. When i looked back to my screen, it had reconnected to the drone and I could then see where it was on the screen again. I flew it around for another 15 minutes or so and brought it back down and landed it manually this time. I am totally amazed by this product. I did a lot of research and read a lot of reviews before buying this drone, and it was well worth it. If you are on the fence, get down off of it and buy this drone!

title: Poor software quality, wifi would not stay connected.
text: I bought this as my first camera drone after seeing some youtube videos that praised it, hoping to save money by going with a less well-known brand name. Ended up returning it. The drone seemed well constructed and flew well, but unfortunately the wifi camera would constantly disconnect from my Samsung Galaxy S8. Apparently Android does not like connecting to unsecured connections without surface and automatically drops them after a minute or two. The wifi would disconnect, but the signal remained strong and I could easily reconnect...but then it would disconnect again within a minute. Got in contact with Ruko support, but they couldn't do much except shrug and say that they have problems with Samsung phones. I tried playing with every advanced setting I could find on my phone but couldn't fix the issue. In addition, the camera positioning motor didn't work well, constantly got stuck and the drone as a whole captures shaky footage due to lack of a gimbal. You get what you pay for. Will most likely shell out more money and get a DJI Mavic Mini.

title: Easy to control

title: Take it slow in learning
text:
My first drone. The first couple of times out I hit trees, a house, and a steel storage container, as well as getting tangled up in some shrubs. The blades still are good. Now have been able to get crashless flights in between bad weather. Looking forward to better weather when I can take it out somewhere besides the back yard.

It is easy to connect to wifi with an Android 10 phone. Battery life is good, 25+ minutes of flying time. I'm still using 'Beginner Mode' so haven't let it venture far from me. It does seem to do well in slight breezes, and the return to home function works well.

Room for improvement in a couple of areas:
The remote control, when first connecting to the phone shows low battery. It seems to take best part of a minute for controller to report the full battery to the android app. The drone battery seems to show properly.
The manual could be improved a bit, especially regarding downloading a map and setting way points.

Bottom line:
Would I buy this drone again. Yes. I recognize it to be limited in some respects, but a great starter that isn't a kid's play toy.

title: Excellent High Quality Drone and Easy to Fly for Beginners and Advanced
text: My Roku drones have been an absolute joy to fly! I first got the U11 and enjoyed it so much I then got the F11 Pro for the increased distance and having an extra drone for my kids to fly with me at the park. I've flown it in some pretty strong cross winds around 15-20mph and it stayed surprisingly stable. The initial setup to calibrate the sensors is a bit of a pain and takes some getting used to but once you get it down it's not a big deal. There's some good Youtube videos out there that walk you through the process pretty well as the instructions aren't as good as having someone show you on video. But once you get that drone up and flying, it is an absolute blast. It's so easy to fly with the GPS keeping it stable and the auto-land function is spot on. Wherever the drone is, once you hit that button it literally lands exactly where it took off from in the exact same orientation. Heck, it's so easy to fly my five year old son was taking off, flying and landing it with hardly any assistance. My brother was so impressed he ended up buying the higher end Ruko F11 GIM that comes with an even better feature packed controller. You do need to get registered with the FAA for this type of drone but the process was easier than I thought. I did it all online with the FAA and it was only $5. Once you get your license number from the FAA you just have to write that number somewhere on all your drones and you're good to fly up to 500 feet as long as it's not over top groups of people. Roku customer service was a great experience as well. The drones come with a card for a free battery after you post a review, I emailed about the free battery for my earlier U11 drone purchase and they sent a free battery right away. Aside from a high quality, feature packed and great priced drone, It's refreshing having a company like this that honors there promises for extra freebies. Thanks Ruko!!! Ruko will be my one stop shop for all my future drone purchases.

text:
You may, or may not have heard about the Ruko F11 Pro. It is a drone with 1 hour of flight time. This drone has some features that you have not seen in other drones. This drone comes with 60 minutes of flight time. That alone is enough to make you buy it. While many of its peers come with battery time of 20 minutes, the F11 Pro triples that. From a single battery, you are going to get 30 minutes of flight time. Since it comes with two batteries, you are going to have double that flight time ‚Äì 60 minutes! To make it even more complete, it comes with powerful brushless motors. These ones will not overheat. It is perfectly possible to do the full 30 minutes of flight time non-stop.

title: Fulfilling entertainment!
text:
After carefully considering the options available, having poured over many reviews, we decided on this drone.
One of the portions of rating, was an a category for beginners. In looking at the amenities of the different models available on amazon, it quickly became evident, that buying something in the low budget area would probably only serve to become something of a frustration. We actually upped our budget to purchase this drone based on the reviews that we have read.
That all being said, this is an amazing and fun form of entertainment. And even beyond that, it will be a useful tool when putting together videos for both personal, and business use.
Setting up and calibrating the unit was easy, and the instructions were clear. It is important to follow the instructions exactly how they say. We are still in the learning curve of the expanded controls, and it is pretty awesome that you can view in real time what the camera is seeing overhead through the app on your phone.
It's important to consider your surroundings when flying, especially when you're learning. The controls are very accurate, and the smallest movement of the joystick will direct the unit in a very responsive way. Equally, until you have a good grasp of the sensitivity of your controls, I would suggest keeping your unit within your site until you've gained enough experience to venture out to its full capacity.
I would definitely recommend this to family and friends that are in the market for a drone. I have wanted one for a few years now, and this has not disappointed.
We are so looking forward to the first camping trip of the summer, as this is one of the reasons that we made this purchase. Being able to see things like we would never see them before in our surroundings. How exciting!

One work around I encountered was that my iPhone 12 Pro Max 5G phone with case was too big for the F11 flight control phone holder. The 5G & 4G both work great with the controller with T-Mobile service in Metro Atlanta. The attached picture shows two containers obtained from the office supply and food storage container areas at Walmart. The work around provided a solution to minimize the impact of sunlight glare on the phone screen while flying the drone and provide a comfortable flight box for the pilot.

text:

I previously had a DJI Phantom that was given to me by my brother. While is was a more expensive drone with more bells and whistles, set up and flying was much more of a learning curve. I eventually crashed it after two week and destroyed it. I was nervous about getting another one but decided to try this one out because of the lower price point. I was worried about the 2 axis cam vs 3 axis cam but figured I would give it a try.

Set up and calibration was easy this morning after becoming familiar with the manual material. Everything works and drone is very responsive. I was able to take of, fly and land with zero issues. Spent about 25 minutes playing with it on my lunch break. VERY happy with the extras on this drone considering the price point. Camera video is GREAT. Over-all very happy with this purchase. title: It is very easy to fly, but the Manual is insufficient to use as a single source reference document.
text:
The F11 Pro is solidly built, a very stable flyer, has superb GPS navigation capability, and great video quality. The 30-minute battery flew for 22-minutes before the low battery alarm sounded providing ample time for the GPS Return-to-Home feature to return the F11 to its takeoff spot.

My rating was 4-Stars because of a very inadequate Flight Manual. It is difficult to read and lacks much detail. Some areas are to brief. What you must do is to research additional sources to gain a full understanding of what this drone will and will not do. It is what you don‚Äôt know that will get you into trouble.

Each strength has a limitation. If you are a ‚Äúquick start ‚Äú guide operator, you are headed for trouble. A good Flight Manual will detail limitations and provide numerous cautions and recovery procedures. This Manual is not adequate for this.

The F11 Pro is very easy and fun to fly. You will be okay with this drone if you go slow and thoroughly understand each area of operations. Just remember, each great feature has a limitation. Be sure to understand what they are and when they occur.

[[VIDEOID:5bc9e23e280f3eeefce7a4e1d789f342]] This drone is awesome!!!! The batteries come fully charge. You will get almost 30 min out of both depending on what you're doing. BUT it's definitely easy if you never flew one. The uploaded video does the view no justice. It's extremely clear but it's a fish bowl view if you're picky.. I don't care, it's clear and it's good enough for me. The range is INSANE! The video is me flying out of my neighborhood over to the next and that was only 140m at 100ft in the air, the max is 1200m!!!!.

Now I gave it 3 stars because today when I flew it (day number 3) It had a couple hiccup's. I flew it out about 100m 80ft and the screen frozen. I exited the app (don't worry you're drone will hover in place until it's given a Command) reopen and the screen was still frozen, had to call it back home. Now don't freak out you're drone will ascend to 100ft before coming back, this just to ensure there's a clear path.

2nd... In follow me mode.. it was flying sideways and wouldn't allow me to straighten it out. Then when I turned around to walk in the other direction. It turned around but swung completely too far out and slammed into the side of my house. So one of feet is slightly slanted but no biggie, it's a replaceable part.

3rd the maps will not open up. The box pops up but it's grey. No arrow, no terrain, just a grey box. So I have to my point of interest the manual way

Update::

I don't if I have a bad drone or not but the max distance I got mines to go up too was about 357 meters and that's at about 100ft in the air. The video freeze and it says radio signal lost, than returns home even though it's showing me a strong signal still.. that's pretty disappointing , especially for the money I spent. I got this drone for the range and it's not even doing half of the distance it's supposed to

Update #2
So after my review of this product, the manufacturer reach out to me personally expressing they're concern in my disappointment. To make it right they're sending me a completely new drone for FREE!!! I have NEVER experience such great customer service in a company. A company that stands proudly behind a product they make. I'm truly excited and can not wait! to receive my new drone!

title: Well built and solid.
text:
This drone was purchased mainly so I could learn about flying a more advanced drone and I was impressed with many things about the product when I received it. Here are some highlights:
1. It is very sturdy and is more stable in the air because of its weight and powerful motors.
2. I have limited testing on the Return feature but so far has landed with inches of the launch point.
3. Speed on this drone in the beginner mode is faster than I thought it would be however it is still easily controllable
4. The written instructions are unambiguous and come on the inside lid of the original box, in the instruction manual, and also on the app and besides, there is a quick-start guide enclosed in the box. The only drawback is the video instructions which are well done, but the voice recording should be re-recorded because the speaker is not a native English speaker, but you don't need that to enjoy your drone anyway.
5. The carrying case easily fits in a backpack or a suitcase and is quite sturdy and has compartments for an extra battery. It is equipped with a strap for easy carrying by hand.
6. I haven't done much with the camera yet but I have been impressed with its low light performance. I would not worry about flying even at dusk if necessary.
I would highly recommend this to anyone who wants a quality drone and does not wish to get into the thousand dollars plus range. Great for learning, great for fun.

title: Great drone for this first timer
text:
This is my second drone but my first time using one. The first drone I got was a different brand and much cheaper. I ended up sending it back after a day. This Ruko F11 Pro, however, has been great. The camera image is clear, I didn't find it to shaky as others have said but I also don't have a comparison. It is easy to control and handle, the GPS feature functions great and keeps the drone in place. I have not gotten a full 30 minutes on the battery but I have been recording, with GPS enabled, and a lot of playing with features. I cannot complain about battery life considering everything that the drone is doing at the time.

I did have an issue with the controller, or I thought I did. The second time I used it the app showed the controller battery was dead. I contacted Ruko about this issue as I felt I had a bad controller. They were quick to respond and explained why they felt the controller was showing a dead/low battery. Basically I did not follow the steps for turning everything on and connecting the phone to the drone WiFi. I tried again, following the steps they outlined in the email which were the same as the instructions, and everything worked great. They asked me to let them know if this worked and if it didn't they would send me a new controller. I felt this was pretty good customer service.

title: Money Well Spent
text: I bought this for my work as I do videography and needed to get some aerial shots for a project I was working on. Wow. First off, I had only briefly flown my son's small drone, and didn't have much experience flying drones, but this Ruko F11 Pro drone is perfect for beginners. Taking off and landing are the hardest parts, but it self-stabilizes itself once you get it into the air. The camera is great, clear photos and videos even at high altitudes. I was very impressed, especially for the price take, I was expecting to have to get a drone well over $500 to get the quality I needed, but this met my criteria at a much lower cost. I had so much fun using it for work, I decided to buy another one for my sons to play with. Also, seems to be very durable because I did happen to fly into a couple objects (tree branch and powerline) and it crashed to the ground, and kept on ticking, although with a few exterior blemishes, and some nicks in the blades, but that just gives it character. Overall, great drone that I recommend. The only negative I would have is that Ruko needs to come out with a drone that has its camera on a 3-axis gimbal for better video action shots and and less swaying during video recording and flying (stopping/ turning).

title: Easy to learn
text:
I have never flown a drone in my life. It took me a couple of tries, and a few restarts, but I was confidently flying this drone by my third session (days apart). Whenever I had a problem (other than the Bluetooth) it was because I forgot one of the steps. The carry case it came with is wonderful because It makes it so easy to pack and take with me. I watched a video with the person using a tablet and I would like to find the accessory to use that with the remote.

Things I would change would be the camera video lens, it has too much of a fish eye lens for my preference. I purchased this drone for photography and art. I love the carry case that came with it, but the cut outs for the extra battery and blades only work when the items stay in the boxes they came in. They are not sturdy boxes, so plan on buying extra foam to help these items stay in place once the boxes have given out.

The first time I crashed into some trees I ended up putting a small chip in one of the blades. The drone still flies great, but I'm monitoring them to see how much abuse they will take. Hopefully I will not add to this soon.

title: Learning curve, but great once you get going.
text:
I bought this as a beginner drone but also to get videos for my YouTube channel, Bay Area Views. I've already started uploading some test footage so if you want to check it out, by all means. Amazon won't let me link to my site, but if you search for "Bay Area Views," you'll be able to see it.

Aside from that shameless plug, this will start you off on "beginners mode," which you can turn off once you get used to things. Beginners mode limits your range and other functionality. You'll need to connect to the drones own wifi on your smartphone in order to view the camera or do any of the fun stuff, but you can still fly it without it.

It is so much fun looking down on yourself from hundreds of feet up. Adjusting the camera, looking around the area, flying around. It even supports VR, although I haven't gotten around to trying it just yet. Gosh, just imaginging VR from sky high altitudes sounds fun!

Camera is slightly fisheye at the edges just so you know what you're getting into. It's kinda like the curvature of the Earth to a higher degree. It's a great little device for beginners but with enough advanced features to keep you entertained and learning for a long time to come!

title: Excellent value and features for the price.
text: As a first time drone pilot I was pleasantly surprised how easy the F11 was to set up and get up in the air. The controls are very intuitive and satellite connection holds the drone steady when hovering and returns to home within a couple of feet of the launch point. The camera works well and video is easy use.  The WiFi connection through the app is also very easy to set up. Flight duration is pretty much as advertised, not quite 30 min but pretty close.  Although the transmitter can control the drone for over a kilometer you will lose the WiFi connection and video through the app at around 500m which can make it difficult to figure out if the drone is flying toward you or further away from you but ‚Äúreturn to home‚Äù will always fly it right back. Overall I‚Äôd highly recommend this drone and for the price, I don‚Äôt think you can do any better. The icing on the cake is Ruko stands behind their product. title: Excellent bundle and quadcopter
text:
After careful research, I selected this Ruko F11 Pro bundle. It was delivered a day earlier than expected - always a plus! It comes in a nice case with space for the drone, extra battery, spare blades and the remote. There is also a zippered compartment which is ideal for the manual and quick start card. The batteries are advertised as lasting 25-28 minutes. In my experience, that is true. Conditions such as wind, speed setting, video use all affect the time.
The drone weighs in at 518 grams. The micro sd card (not included) needs to be 32gb or less. The camera lens is very wide - 120 degrees. The video saved on the sd card is 2K, video saved on phones is 720 (samples attached).
Control is easy to master and the remote is responsive. All the the features (GPS, Follow Me, Point of Interest, etc. work as advertised.
I have been very pleased with the features and performance of this drone!

title: One of if not thee best drone in the market.
text:
This is one, if not thee easiest drone to date that I have piloted and goofed around on. The video quality is clear and crisp with not much lag or shacking when using your phone to virtually see through the drones camera. I did notice when I used my phone (Samsung Note 20 ultra 5g) I had longer range and better connectivity then I was to use my son's phone (iphone 8) that dropped the connectivity about 1/2 to 2/3rds the distance. I have bought the company's other drone the u11 for fun and it outperformed my expectations especially the GPS feature when I would lose signal flying to far or when the wind would pick up and take my drone away (living in Seattle during the winter) the GPS would kick in and fight its way back to where I toke off from and hover right where I would be standing requesting to land. I have had it stuck in the rain mid flight and gotten it home safe with no issues even though it's not recommended to fly in the rain if you get stuck in a down pour it'll be OK just get it back to land home and dry it off and you shouldn't have any issues, I haven't and I flown several times in the rain cause let's face it we all are kids at heart and want to play with our new toys all the time that's why we get them.

Overall this is the best high quality drone I personally flown for a low-mid budget price out there and I flown several r/c planes, drones, quadcopters, helicopters if the price is just a little to much and your unsure how you will be piloting a drone then I suggest to try out the Ruko U11 first and get a feel with the GPS feature and then step it up if you wish with this drone. Tmhe sizes are slightly different as seen in the photo I toke but overall same security feeling knowing your drone will Come home back to you and not go flying into the sunset never to be seen again, until you watch the news and see it being reported come crashing down hitting a jogger or bicyclist in the head.

title: Easy set up, intuitive controls... only complaint is remote battery life
text: Received as Christmas gift.  I charged it over night and did my first 4 runs the next day.  Setup:  Follow the instructions closely.  They are not the best instructions, but if you read it closely and follow step by step, this really is an easy set up.  Tip:  Use the Ruko 2 page start up card when setting up and download the app before you start (search for SJ GPS Pro).  Flight:  The first time, I didnt use my app.  That was dumb.  Flip up the phone clasp in the middle of the remote and use the app, much more intuitive for me than the remote as I am getting used to everything.  Also, be mindful of the preset flight parameters (only configurable via the app as far as I can tell) as they are set for "beginner mode".  Once you get the hang of things, you will want to increase the distance and altitude (I believe you must do so when connected to the drone).  Remote:  So far, the remote has been the limiting factor on flight time. After my 3rd flight (a total of 15 mins max), the remote started beeping as the power was low.  I then didn't have control of the drone and it just hovered (at a very high altitude), I hit the down controls... nothing... I hit return to home... nothing... so I ran back inside and connected the remote to the charger and hit return to home and by the time I got outside, it was coming down to the launching point.  Thankfully, I wasn't in some remote area with no power.  Could have been user error by not charging the remote enough, but I will carry a powerbank with me when I take it out.  Overall, after 4 flights, I would say this thing is pretty awesome for beginners.  My primary problem is that I can see myself wanting to upgrade pretty quickly!

text:
As the title states, this is my first drone. I figured the price point would provide a good amount of quality and function for a beginner pilot who's liable to crash it. (So far I haven't crashed it!!)

The camera is rather good, no complaints there. The range is impressive; it's more than I'd probably ever require but is definitely a nice option to have. The stability of the drone isn't 100% perfect, especially in windy conditions, but for the price, I'd say it's more than adequate (like 95% perfect). The controls are slightly tricky at first, at least for an absolute beginner. However, after one or two test flights, I feel quite confident in my piloting abilities. Also, the extra functions (ex: target tracking, route mapping) are unexpectedly nifty and work like a charm!

Additionally, the customer support has been very helpful and quick to reply. 5/5 stars on that front.

Overall, I think this is a great drone for beginners or intermediates who want a great balance of quality vs. price. Definitely satisfied with my purchase.

title: Great drone
text:
I've had this drone for a few months now and it has worked very well. I am using my Motorola phone and have not had any issues with connections. It connects every time. This is my first drone and I am very happy with how easy it is to fly and land. I have flown it in winds as high as 20 mph gusts and it is more challenging to fly but seems to handle it fine. I received an email from the seller right after I purchased it and they are very polite and prompt in answering questions. I recently thought I was having a battery problem with the remote and sent them an email. I had a response within hours with things for me to try and if it did not help they would take care of it. It ended up being a mistake on my part so I'm up and flying again. The customer service is great and in my opinion one of the most important things when purchasing. If you have a great product and no service, better hope it never fails.

I chose to purchase this drone after looking at the Mavic pro for some time. I just could not get myself to spend that much more for my first drone but also didn't want to just waist money on something that would be of no use. This drone is great and will help me better know what I truly need for my applications prior to spending more money. With this said, this drone had a nice camera but it is not gymbled. If you are hovering over your target or just taking scenic video it is not much of a problem. But I takes work to move it into place and have the good photo angle since when you move the drone it changes the camera angle. It also does not have any sensors which is not much of an issue for me since I am not flying it to far away from me and can still see where it is. If you plan on flying it far or in tight areas, that would be a needed feature.

I highly recommend this drone for a first timer or if you are not completely sure of what options you rally need. As I progress in my needs and get the funds to upgrade I probably will. This will make a great backup or the one I can have my kids work with so if there is a large mistake it will not be as large of a loss.

title: Easy to Fly Beginner Drone. Good App. Thanks Ruko!
text:
UPDATE: got a third drone from Ruko. Happy with the end result, despite the turbulent start. HAPPY FLYING !

Actually flew two of these. The first one flew OK, stable flight, but wouldn't land properly. Thing is, it arrived with only one battery and was supposed to have two batteries. Amazon wouldn't send just a battery replacement, so I had to return for a whole new replacement unit. The second Ruko drone did not fly properly. The calibration appeared to be off, so the control stick steered unpredictably. Several times the drone seemed to have a mind of its own and flew off at high speed in random directions. Finally it crashed itself into a parking lot and broke into tiny pieces. I suspect I'm in the minority, it seems like it has potential to be a good product. I bought it because the price was good for a beginner drone, and I wouldn't mind crashing it eventually, just let me crash it on my own, not from a control malfunction.

title: Perfect beginner drone
text: This is the best beginner drone you can buy. It has GPS, 4k camera and 1080p video. Several options such as waypoints, and follow-me movements. Turn drone on, turn remote on, turn WiFi on your phone and open app. Connect to your drone via WiFi. Once connected, you have to follow instructions to setup the drone and calibrate via the app. After the initial setup, it's amazing. After you get more familiar and comfortable with flying, you can turn beginner mode off and fly further distances. The distance is incredible, however, it has to be line of sight. If you lose line of sight, you will most likely lose control of the drone. If you ever lose control or go beyond the set distance, it will return and land exactly where it took off from.

text:
I got my A11 to install Ham Radio Antennas in tall trees and to inspect existing antennas such as the one shown in the pictures. It works great with an add-on drop-device to release a lead sinker and fishing line into the tree canopy. The fishing line is then used to hoist heavier antenna guy lines.

I'll offer a few suggestions here: In my search for a drone, I read many stories how they just flew away never to be seen again, on the first time out. With that in mind, I first labeled all the controls as shown in the picture. Even then, it was still confusing, but after 3 days of play at low elevation around my yard I got the hang of it. Only then did I go up to 100ft as shown in the attached pictures. I also picked a wind-still day which I recommend for precision positioning. On windy days you can expect some wobble while the drone corrects to GPS.

title: The perfect beginner drone
text:
[[VIDEOID:28d2e306c56f78770642c4b08b956cea]] There's a lot to love with this drone, and very little not to love. If you've never bought a drone before and you're thinking about getting this one: just do it! You wont regret it.

This thing is super easy to fly, super fun to fly, packed with features, and has an amazing camera! Having 30 minutes of flight time on each battery is plenty to get good videos/pictures, and swapping them out is trivially easy.

I will say, however, that recording video directly to my Galaxy S10 will only give me videos in 720p. This really isn't too big of a deal though, because it will record in 2K to an SD Card.

Speaking of the SD Card, I couldn't seem to actually find anywhere in the manual that talked about where to put an SD Card into the Drone! So, I've uploaded a picture with this review to show you where it should be. Wasn't too hard to figure out, but it definitely had me confused for a second.

=== Flight Quality ===

I bought this drone for myself for Christmas, and thus have only flown for a little bit during the winter here in Washington State. This means cold temperatures, bits of rain/snow, and pretty modest winds. I have had no trouble with this thing fighting the wind at all. There was one occasion where I attempted to fly it before allowing to get a good GPS signal, which caused it to drift a bit during takeoff, however that was my mistake for being in such a rush, and it quickly figured out where it was and stabilized. Overall, I am extremely impressed with how accurate the GPS is on this drone, especially since I am mostly flying it out in the sticks where GPS seems to usually have problems.

=== Camera Quality ===

The camera is absolutely nothing to laugh at. Having such a wide FOV allows you to get some pretty seriosuly good looking landscape shots, and recording videos on 2K is beautiful. However, I definitely recommend using video editing software to remove the fish eye effect from the wide FOV, and to fix some of the shakiness that can occur while the drone is flying. I've also found that videos will want to automatically color correct, which can be a small annoyance.

=== Features ===

I think I use the waypoint feature every single time I fly this drone. It is absolutely phenomenal, and lends itself to taking beautiful panning shots. I haven't used the other features quite as much, but when I have. I've found them very straightforward, and they worked very well. Additionally, I once tried to film a sunrise by positing the drone above my backyard pointed east, then leaving the controller and walking inside. It filmed for about ten minutes, then suddenly lost signal. I was pretty paranoid about this the whole time, so I was able to find my drone and get reconnected right away. However, when I did, i noticed that it simple flew back over my house to where I had launched it, then begun landing itself. If I had done nothing, I could have simply walked outside and found my drone perfectly safe sitting where I launched it. This is a huge peace of mind feature for me, and I was really impressed with how well it worked. Kudos to SJRC for that one.

text:
Update: I have updated my review based upon the customer service I received. I was contacted by their service team who arranged to send me a replacement drone. I was impressed by their quick response.

Ok folks, I had this thing long enough to charge the battery and go through the pre flight set up. It was set to safety mode so should have not gone further than 30m. Well, it was working great for about 10 minutes. Then after landing and taking off a couple times, the next time I took off it made a noise at me and rose about 40 or 50 meters in the air and then started flying off towards the west. It rose high enough to clear the trees in the surrounding area and disappeared into god knows where.

Long story short be careful, though I am not sure how to be careful if the safety protocols don't work. Maybe have a shirt or something on hand to chuck at it if it tries to do what happened to me, maybe you will get lucky. Fastest 250ish I spent for about 20 minutes of fun. text: I've owned several drones throughout the past few hours, primarily Holystone drones, and a couple Potensic, and let me tell you this one takes the cake. This drone has the battery life you would expect in a higher end drone, and its extremely durable. I've crash it twice now, and she still flies like a beauty. It's a great beginner drone, I have no problem teaching my 9 and 10 year old siblings how to use it, especially since it has a beginners mode which restricts the drones range and prevents it from flying away. The drone has a phenomenal camera, I was all around surprised with how well the drone consistently delivers all of the features that a higher end drone would, without any sacrifices to the quality. Holy stone, and Potensic can't say the same for their drones, which are similarly priced and lack many of the great features this drone does given the price range. Overall  I'm happy with my purchase, and I look forward to the next flight with my Ruko F11 Pro Drone.

title: Good Drone - For the most part
text:
I've had this drone for almost one month now.

In the month I took it out 4 times.

First Flight went without a hitch.

Second Flight, the drone struggled in some wind. I activated the return to home, and it started to come back. However, when it had reached approximately 25 feet from me, it it had gone into a POI Orbit, and spiraled down till it crashed from around 4 feet off the ground. Let me explain a little: I had gone off roading, and had a clear view below and around me, no one in sight, No Power lines, no WiFi interference, cell data yes. I had ONLY activated the Return to Home function, and released the sticks of the controller maintaining line of sight the entire time.

I had contacted Ruko due to the weird return to home incident.

My next flight was 6 days later, fully charged batteries. the first 23mins battery was fine, no problems. The second battery was installed, drone was sent out to the same areas as it was just a few minutes ago. During Hover, hands off the sticks, drone banked suddenly and hard crashed into the side of small mountain. Live Video showed what appeared to be a cracked lens. I was able to use the GPS map to retrieve my drone, no visible signs of damage to the drone or camera. Except for the drone felt HOT to touch. After letting the drone cool down at home, and recharging my battery, I decided to power it up and check the camera. I was surprised it powered on, motors spooled right up, and image was undamaged. However, the camera could not pitch down, or pitch up (when manual adjustment)

Next flight was a week later, I had replaced the camera. Again, first 23mins of flight (battery) was good, no problems. It was not until the 2 second battery did the drone exhibit incorrect response to stick movements.

Example; I applied forward stick, the drone went backwards to the right; Back stick, forward to the left. Not sure what had happened since I changed nothing, except to put in a fresh battery. Controllers charge was still almost full, according to the app on my mobile phone.

I have heard back from Ruko about the weird return to home, and they of course said there was nothing wrong in the data log for that flight. So, I am not sure what to think.

Picture quality:
it is advertised as 4K; lol, even my mobile phone reports it as only 1080p video and photos.

Return to home:
even after calibration, and satellites check on app; when it lands, it is over 3feet from the landing pad, in NO winds.

It was easy to learn because when you let go of the controls the drone stays stable in the air where it was, and you can read the instructions and continue with your flight or with the new feature you just read about like Follow Me, and the drone will follow you around your neighborhood on your bike. This came with 2 batteries and, using video length as a timer, they both average 24 minute flights. I figure that as a beginner you waste energy and the flights will be longer once I'm more gentle on the controls. The return button works as advertised; the drone flies straight up to its max height, goes directly over its starting point, and comes straight down to land within 2 feet of where it launched. This has been lots of fun for me and my friends; one of those friends bought one for himself.

title: Buy this drone - stop looking & comparing, just click "buy" and fly happy
text:
Its not often that I'm surprised, well, there was that one time my grandma vaulted over a mini-pony to get to the last cream-puff before the dog ate it, but aside from that, its unusual. In this case though I can say without hesitation that I was surprised. Given the vast list of features that typically demand premium prices, to say nothing of the case, battery and folding functionality, I figured costs had to have been cut somewhere - like propellers are extra or you're only buying a picture of the drone, with a scratch and sniff sections where you can smell the summer breeze that you'd be flying in.....if you had propellers. It was with no small surprise then and all too rare bested expectations, when I opened the box to find the F11 Pro every bit the quality machine its claimed to be. The build quality is exceptional, it feels twice the price you pay. There's nothing cheap or flimsy about this aerial juggernaut, in fact before the flight test I wondered if something so....robust....could actually lumber into the air, let alone fly - but I'd be proved wrong on that score. Everything looks carefully crafted, form and function by design and purpose, as opposed to whatever injection mold was kicking around the shop. The case is good, everything fits well and even here, something that is often an afterthought thing "thrown in" you can see there is attention to detail and a bias toward doing it right.

Unfolding the drone takes a bit of thought - I mean, not Mensa-level, but there is an order to it, and in another nod to quality, you're going to need to apply some effort - not "Earl, get the sledge" effort, but the "arms" positively move into place and you won't be doing it with one finger - unless you have a really strong finger, like a body-builder, but just your finger....like your finger works out, but the rest of you doesn't. Unfolding the controller is actually as near a work of art as unfolding a controller can be - reminds me of a transformer...auto-bot, obviously.

Lets get down to brass-tacks though because as Humphrey Bogart once said, "design doesn't add up to a hill of beans in this crazy town, if the drone won't fly" - I'm not sure Bogart said anything even close to that actually, but if they had drones in 1942, he would have - but I digress. The start-up procedure for this drone is a little more involved than some lesser models, where the start-up procedure is basically "turn it on". This however is a more sophisticated machine and so your "pre-flight" is going to be more involved as well - and you want it to be.....it means the drone has complex systems, and just like any pre-flight check, its important to know that they are working and calibrated. That said, its relatively simple -basically comprised of turning in a circle and moving the control sticks - the instructions, app and quick-start guide on the inside of the box lid all do a great job of walking you through it.

Flying this drone is is what drone flying should be, but so often isn't. I have four drones and at least half are fair-weather only. Did someone sneeze fourteen miles away? Best not fly because the drone will be sent careening into a hedge. What's that?a perfect day with no wind? great....lets get our 8 minutes of flying in. Seriously, some drones seem more designed to have you take up another hobby, than fly drones. Fortunately, the F11 Pro makes flying fun. First, it laughs in the face of a breeze - it is basically a flying brick folks, and bricks don't take shtick from any mere gust of wind. Second, it will fly for about 28 minutes on a battery....28 minutes... that's almost 29 minutes, which is almost 30! AND you get a second battery in the box....so ....take 28, carry the four, find the square root of your mom's meatloaf and TADA!.....near as makes no difference, an hour of flight...IN THE BOX. I found all the flight features to be better than expected and more fun than I had thought - better yet though, is that you can actually fly this drone properly, outside, in the real world, and for longer than it takes some kid to say "hey nice drone, can I fly it"? To which you must automatically respond "Heck no kid, buzz off,...and.....tell mommy I'm on an important call, not to be disturbed for another 27 minutes".

I won't go into all the features, you can read them yourself, they are there, they work. What is important here though is that this drone is worth every penny you spend, and yes, it is more expensive than some lesser models, but those are the ones that don't fly well, or crash if uncle Dave toots in your general direction. It also flies for a long time, in a way that's controllable and adjustable for varied skill - and not just because it can go faster or slower, but because it has multiple features designed to make you successful and enjoy flying, almost as if that were the point.

I have no affiliation with the brand, I bought the drone with my own hard-earned cash and I write reviews for products that deserve them.

text:

The 4-year old was almost immediately able to fly it and he loves the "return and land" feature. He thinks that's very cool. My 2.5-year old had a little more trouble but that's mostly because he just doesn't have fine motor control so he's jerky on the controller. But even he was able to fly it.

I didn't understand the beginner mode at first but, now that I do, it's a great feature. Basically, with it on you can't lose the drone. It hits 30 meters and just reverses. It means I don't have to worry about the boys accidentally flying past their sight.

The camera features work well. Took a bunch of pictures and texted them to Grandma and the Uncles.

The flight time seems about accurate. With the two charged batteries we basically played until I was tired, even if the boys wanted to go longer.

If you're looking for a fun, solid, well-built, drone at a reasonable price look no further.

title: Good drone
text:
This is a good drone but it falls short of my expectations for its price point. The frame feels solid, it's easy to fly, and I love the micro-USB charging for the batteries & controller; however, there have been several issues.

I've had the F11Pro for a few days now and have only had one minor 'crash' (one of the rotors accidentally hit the end of a tree branch and the drone fell ~4-5 feet to the ground onto grass). This is the only incident I had with the drone and upon inspection I found multiple issues:
1. One of the blades was bent and had to be replaced.
2. The plastic cover over one of the lights is cracked.
3. The camera housing came off and had to be reassembled.

The crash was extremely minor and the above damages seem disproportional. I'm disappointed in the product stability. I also have the Holy Stone HS-175 and it has been through larger accidents with barely a scratch! I have concerns over the longevity of the F11 Pro and will update my review once I fly more.

UPDATE: manufacturer reached out to me and replaced my device. They were super friendly and helpful - so far no complaints :)

title: This drone is AMAZING!!
text:
[[VIDEOID:59177621955a767a022a36ff080de1dd]] This is only my second drone, but I've flown both of them quite a bit, plus done a TON of research, watched videos, talked to people who own drones, etc. My first drone was $100 model with a fixed camera and about a 10-minute runtime per battery and a 1080p camera.

The first thing I want to say about this little beauty is WOW! Seriously. I mean the fact that it folds, fist nicely and compact into it's included carrying case and comes with two batteries is nice, but...none of those are the reasons that you buy a drone. You want stability, ease of use, long flight times and quality pics/vids. Well, this little drone has all of that.

Camera - The resolution of the photographs is pretty awesome, in my opinion. The video is high-quality, as well. Check out my uploads. Also, I love the fact that the camera tilts a full 90-degrees. Cheaper drones have fixed cameras or only tilt 70-degrees, which is ok, but I prefer to position the camera to make the shot, not the drone to make the shot. Plus, with fixed cameras, the position of the camera tends to make the pictures/videos dark because of the compensation for the sun being almost directly into the lens. The fact that the camera doesn't have pan capability is no big deal, because when you have the controls in "slow" mode, the side-to-side and rotation motions are quite smooth. The only "con" that I can come up with is the 120-degree lens. Because it's somewhat panoramic, it tends to give pics/vids a bit of a fish eye effect. Not so much that it's annoying, but it exists.

Battery life - Runtimes are between 23-28 minutes, with mine, anyway. Drone runtimes can vary even within the same model, so yours may get a couple more minutes or a couple less. Either way, it's long enough to get a ton of enjoyment out of and when the battery dies; you let the motors cool off for about ten minutes and send it up with the second battery (included with my purchase).

Controls - It has three speed positions (slow, normal, fast). It defaults to normal when you turn it on, which is great for general flying. Switch it to slow for smooth-scrolling video panning. Go to fast when you want to get there in a hurry. It has First Person View capability through your smartphone, with 5g WiFi, which is great. The connection is solid and you get very little video stutter (unless you're panning really fast, which is bad practice anyway). I like being able to see what the camera sees, when it sees it. The app for your phone defaults to "beginner mode" until you turn it off. Beginner mode only lets fly about 30m up and about that far away. It's great when you're first starting out, but you'll probably want to switch to the highest limits by the end of the first battery (It's that easy to fly, even for beginners).

Stability - This is where this baby shines!! It is ROCK SOLID in the air. I've had it up to it's 120m altitude limit (governed by the firmware) in moderate wind, and the only way you'd notice that it's windy is with a good gust. The GPS super stable and when you let go of the control sticks in video mode, you'd swear you were taking still shots.

I can't even begin to say enough good stuff about this little drone. Don't let the price and the size of it fool you. It's well constructed, rock-solid stable in the air, easy to fly, has long runtimes, and a fantastic tilting camera. Sure, you can pay $1800+ for a Mavic Pro 2 or a Phantom, but unless you're a professional drone videographer, you're not going to see a remarkable difference enough to shell out that kind of dough. On the other end of the spectrum, I don't recommend getting a cheaper drone first. Which is what I did. Even though this drone has more features and is more expensive than starter drones, the fact that it's so easy to fly will make you wish that you had gotten it first. You're going to buy it eventually anyway, so why not make it your next ( or first). And for around $300 (what I paid at the time), you can't go wrong.

title: Mechanical malfunction lost our Drone
text: Just now getting around to writing an update. We got the drone initially with an issue and we were sent a replacement. We were also sent a form to have another 30 min battery sent to us for our drone for free. Had the new drone a couple weeks, used it just a handful of times and never long enough to drain the one battery so my husband hadn‚Äôt yet put in the second battery. Long story short, we took the drone fully charged with our kids to the park. It is a large open field and we flew it around using the first battery up. When we insert the second battery onto the drone we raised it up into the air and all hell broke loose. The Drone literally became what I would call possessed. It started flying in circles and nothing we did on the controller would get it down. We lost all control. The drone after flying in circles shot up and off. My son ran as fast as he could but it was gone, we searched for days and even put an add online for a reward if found. I am so disappointed that we only got to use it a handful of times and that it appears something in the second battery took over once inserted on drone. It flew so far off it lost all service and communication and has yet to be found. A lot of money to spend for something like this to happen mechanically and lose the product for good.

title: The Sub-$300 Price Tag Simply Cannot be Beaten
text:
The Ruko F11 Pro Drone is, to say the least, impressive. The F11 boasts a host of features, including a compact, foldable design, a sturdy, muscular body that feels comfortable and "rich" in one's hands, an integrated GPS module, 3 advanced flight modes, including Follow Me and Orbit, a Return to Home function, and an adjustable Ultra-High Definition (UHD) 4K camera that compels attention.

The drone is easy to operate and maneuver, even for the neophyte pilot. Takeoff and landing are a breeze and the F11 Pro even has the ability to hover independently, allowing the pilot to either contemplate his next move, familiarize himself with the controls, or simply admire the power and beauty of the craft. The drone ships with two 2500mAh batteries, allowing a more-than-adequate 60 minutes combined flight time. Additionally, the pilot is also kept abreast of the battery status of both the drone and the transmitter via the downloadable SJ GPS PRO app. The app also provides all the in-flight details of the drone in addition to a quick start guide, troubleshooting notes, GPS, photo, video, and other controls.

Videos are recorded in sharp, crisp, and clear 2.9K while photographs are captured at a vivid 4K. The GPS module and the transmitter both provide controls that may be used to adjust the camera remotely. The 120-degree field of view, especially when coupled with the in-built Orbit Mode, can be combined to produce compelling video footage. The Ruko F11 Pro can also record live video with its 5GHz First-person View (FPV) capabilities at up to 500M (1640 ft.). For the cinematographer on a budget, or for those just getting into drone videography, the sub-$300 price tag simply cannot be beaten.

NOTE: To truly appreciate some of these features, the SJ GPS PRO app is essential. Consumers should also keep in mind that a dual-band (2.4-5G) smartphone is required. That being said, neither the app nor GPS is necessary for flight, photo, or video recording. GPS, for example, is needed in case the drone gets out of the pilot's line-of-sight. The pilot can use the built-in Return to Home feature to locate and return the craft to its takeoff origin. That being said, another excellent feature is its Headless Mode which orients the drone to the pilot's location thus avoiding it getting lost. GPS is also needed for WayPoint mapping. Moreover, for legal operation in the USA, the Ruko F11 drone needs to be registered with the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) due to its weight of 520G (18.3 oz.).

In closing, the Ruko F11 Pro Drone is great for the beginner, expert, or professional. It is durable with a muscular, albeit non-bulky body of 17.5 in. x 15.9 in. x 3.2 in. with an open frame. And a 7 in. x 4 in. x 3.2 in. folded frame. It is quick, has a 2.4 GHz frequency transmitter with a maximum range of 1219M (3999 ft.), and can climb to heights of 120 m (393 ft.). The whisper-quiet brushless motors are powerful and maintain a cool temperature even after extended flight duration. The drone is delivered in a handsome carrying case, comes with extra blades, screws, and a small hex wrench for blade replacement, should that time come.

Are there any drawbacks? The only two disbenefits that I can proffer at the time of this writing are the lack of a gimbal stabilizer and the inevitable barrel distortion due to the camera's ultra-wide-angle lens. While there is no getting around the issue with the lack of gimbal stabilizer‚Äînecessary to maintain a level in-flight camera‚Äîthe barrel effect is a small expense; one that can easily be corrected in post-production with the image editing software of one's choice.

If you are considering getting into drone piloting, aerial photography, or videography, the Ruko F11 Pro Drone is a great starting point. It provides the perfect combination of cost-effectiveness, ease-of-use, and quality that more than warrants the decision to purchase.

title: Fun to fly little drone
text: Got the Ruko F-11 Pro Drone a while ago and had to wait for cold weather to clear and high winds to cease. Finally got to go out and run the F-11 through a couple of batteries and was pleasantly surprised on how well the quad-copter flew. The battery provides long flight time more than your typical drone.  This quad is very quick to set up and the provided check list makes it quick to get up and flying. The aircraft easily lifts off and holds position in one spot. Connection to a cell phone is good and shows camera image and a wide range of control settings and information.  There is a beginner mode that limits distance and control speed. The beginner mode is nice to test things out without too much excitement. It there is a wind, letting off the controls stops the drone in a couple of feet, but under control, the wind will carry you away if you don't get on the controls.  After you realize the GPS disables with control, you get the idea. Even at that, in a panic, release the control levers and the GPS takes over stopping the drone in a stable, one place, hover.  There is a thumb wheel that lets you set other more advanced control at will and puts the drone into a quicker and more nimble control bringing out the true fun of the machine. Even in respectable wind, the drone is stable and easy to control. The phone app has a lot of settings and interesting settings like follow mode and orbit to play with. You will not quickly get bored with this quad.  The camera produces decent images and video and the single axis camera gimble lets you get forward or straight down pictures with the turn of a second thumb wheel. The drone looks fascinating suspended in space while flying.  All in all a slightly more advanced aircraft at a fairly reasonable price.

title: Most Bang for Your Buck
text: I have been flying remote controls airplanes and helicopters for over 10 years and for some reason never jumped on the drone bandwagon the last 4-5 years until now. Finally pulled the trigger on a Black Friday special and couldn‚Äôt be happier. The learning curve is basically non existent compared to flying RC planes due to the GPS assistance. The drone literally flys itself anytime  you release the sticks on the controller. The app was very user friendly and from unboxing to flying was less than 10 minutes. I have about 10 flights so far and everything has been perfect. Pictures are crisp and video quality is good. There is no camera gimbal so there is a little jello effect if the winds are high or you have maxed out the altitude but at reasonable height and distant from the focal point the quality exceeded my expectations for this price point. Great entry to mid level drone to get ones feet wet before going all in on a $1000 plus model. Very pleased with the purchase and would buy again with no reservation.

text: I received my F11 Pro today and I am very pleased with the way it was shipped. The carrying case is well designed and sturdy. The drone itself appears to be very well made and I do like that the props are two piece, free spinning, less likely to damage when crashed, notice I said when not if.... Flying is quite simple, it works with my phone, samsung s-10+, but I have to take it out of the life proof case to fit, not a biggie.  I am looking forward to making great videos with this drone and am very pleased with it.

title: What a great purchase! This drone is awesome!
text:
This drone is awesome! Flying it is pretty simple once you get the hang of it, and the beginner mode allows for you to take it easy and not get too far away. The come home button is an awesome feature to have too, and the picture/video quality from the camera is excellent. This is absolutely worth every penny! I am so happy with this and can not wait to get it out further and further to see everything around us and what our property looks like from the air.
I did a lot of research on drones but I kept coming back to this one. It has everything I was looking for; foldable, POI, way point flight, return to hone, object tracking, 30 min flight time, 4K and a hell of a lot more. I read some neg reviews about the app, but it works perfect for me (galaxy s9+). Incredibly easy to fly. In fact you just tell it what to do and it does it. The drones that cost about $1000 more do have a few features that this one lacking. Like obstacle avoidance. But honestly, this is so easy to fly, I don't know why you would need it. Anyway, do yourself a favor, get the F11 Pro. At this price, I don't think anything else comes close.
This drone can fly by itself, mostly. Take off and lands by a touch of a button. Comes home and lands with a touch of a button. If you panic during flight just let go of the controls and it just hovers waiting for you to resume control. The camera is great also. Gives a bird's eye view of your surroundings or first person pilot mode. You can clearly see and make out objects from 250 feet + high. We are glad we waited about a year before buying our first drone. This was mainly due to short flying times unless you sent close to $1000 or more. What's the point if you can only fly 15 minutes at a time. By the time you get used to the drone, times up, dead battery. This one goes for 25+ minutes and comes with 2 batteries. It flies high enough, fast enough, long enough with great views so you can actually enjoy the thing. I highly recommend this product!

title: Drone is great for beginners!
text: I received this drone as a Christmas present. Due to the weather, I wasn't able to fly the drone for a few days. I found the instructions for set-up very easy to follow, and I was able to get up and flying within about 10 minutes. The drone is very easy to control, and the return to home function works great. As a beginner I highly recommend using the auto take-off and landing feature, but taking off and landing is easy even if you don't use the push button function. I find that the batteries do last approximately 30 minutes each, but can be  shorter if you are flying in the wind. The camera and video functions both work very well, and I have gotten some excellent photos. I have had a few times where I have flipped the drone over on landing and the drone is very durable. Each of those issues was me not getting the props turned off fast enough. My ids have also each flown the drone and had no problems learning as well.

text: Bought this for myself for Christmas.  The drone comes in a very nice case and  is really compact when folded up. It is set on beginning mode which limits the speed, altitude and distance it can travel.  Probably a good thing for most beginners.  It can easily be adjusted in the future via you smart phone.  The basic functions work really well and when the weather gets a little better I will try some of the more advanced functions. I did by accident remove the GPS during my first flight and the drone took off by itself.  I was able to get it under control and bring it back but be careful not to start  hitting unknown buttons while learning to fly.  The quality of the pictures and video were very good.  Overall, based on the restrictions of staying within line of sight for hobby flyers I believe this drone is perfect.  Highly recommend this drone for beginners and intermediate folks.

title: Excellent Drone for Beginners
text:
Received the drone on a Saturday, practiced a couple of hours in the afternoon and by the next day had pretty well mastered. If you are looking for a drone that is nice for both beginners or even intermediate flyers, this is the drone for you. It includes many features such as, RTH, Headless mode, Follow me and some features such as hand gestures I doubt I will ever use but it's there if you want. The camera takes excellent videos and photos for a drone in this price range due to its 2K camera. And it's works great and in tandem with a mobile phone app that is available so you can actually have a live view of what the drones camera is seeing.

On the one I received, I cannot get the controller to turn off. Instructions say to hold down power button for 1 second to turn on and 2 seconds to turn off. When on, I can hold down the power button for 15-20 seconds and the controller will never go off. Not a deal killer because I usually charge the controller once I'm finished flying but I do wish it worked correctly.

Be advised there is one feature that much more expensive drones employ is there is no object avoidance so always be aware of where to drone is. All in all, a great purchase for a first time drone flyer without spending an arm and a leg and much better than the little toy drones.

Update: Contacted the seller about the controller not turning off. Response with quick and very helpful. To turn off press the power button once and then hold down a second time. Instructions were not clear on that but they actually sent a video of how to turn off. Later in the day the drone flew off at a high rate of speed and I had no control. It slammed into the side of a house and one of the arms broke off. I'm working with customer service now on what could have happened and any remedies and will update this review with their response.

title: Maddening setup; Android app does not work; Company paying buyers for positive reviews
text:
First of all, beware any positive reviews. The drone comes with a card indicating they'll send you a free battery in exchange for a positive review.

I found this drone exasperating. In 2020, I would expect that the thing "just works." Not so here. I unpacked the device, and went through the instructions. Before you fly, there are several steps you need to go through - I wasn't aware this is common in low end drones, so that was a surprise but a trade-off I could live with. You should expect about 10 minutes of jockeying with the thing to get it calibrated, if all goes well (which it won't).

The first step is to connect the drone to the remote control by moving the joysticks in a certain way. It took several cycles of turning the remote and drone on/off to get it to connect - I almost gave up and returned the device as defective. The other calibration steps are easier, but be prepared to do each step multiple times to get it to "take."

I spent about 90 minutes over two attempts to get the device ready to fly with the remote only. I tried to connect the app at several times throughout the process. My phone connected to the drone's wifi just fine. I downloaded the app from the QR code in the manual, but this exact model was not available in the selection menu. The app would not connect to the drone at any point in the process. I have a Pixel 5 running stock Android 11.

So I am beyond frustrated - I sunk a lot of time into this, but I'm not willing to go through a tear-your-hair-out process every time I get it out. It clearly does not work with Android; the calibration steps (about 8 steps) take multiple attempts to work at each step; and the positive reviews here are incentivized. I feel taken for a ride.

Finally, this device is also clearly intended for the Chinese market and poorly transferred to the US. The manual has spelling errors, and the Android app has links that direct you to videos in Chinese. Support is only available during overnight hours (after 9pm EST) - I'm not opposed to support staff being based overseas, particularly at this price point - but they really should be available during daylight hours in their target market.

I left one star because I think on paper this is a great device. Specs are great for the price, and included 2nd battery and spare rotors is nice.

title: Did not disappoint!
text:
Struggling to find fun adventures with my teen boys, I happened upon a man flying a drone this past weekend in a local park. We stopped to chat, as he flew. He was very gracious with his time and showed me the drone and the capabilities. I had never shopped for a drone before, and figured the price would be too high for my current budget. I was wrong. Lucky for me, he was flying a Ruko F11, so I ordered the same one and it arrived two days later. Me and the boys have been flying it non-stop ever since. We love it.

Take some time to review the instructions and watch some of the videos prior to flight. After that, keep the handy Quick Start Guide with you during the first couple flights. That brief 'training' was all I needed. The drone was very stable and worked perfect. Having GPS capabilities has been very helpful getting the drone to return to the exact take off location with a push of the button. I am experimenting with the Way Point feature, and have programmed several flights around the neighborhood. It is a fun tool and very easy to use. I got some great photos of the setting sun.

I would highly recommend this drone for anyone interested in have some quality time with their kids. The quality seems top notch, it is easy to use and the battery life impressed me. No need to spend 4X more to have a great time. With Christmas quickly approaching, I will probably be purchasing another specifically for my boys.

title: Best Drone I have ever had!
text: If you are in the market for a state of the art drone, trust me buy this one.  Amazing engineering, software and product!

title: Great pictures, videos, and fun to fly!
text:
My first drone was a Contixo brand. I returned it to Amazon because it arrived with one DOA battery and on the 2nd and 3rd flights it just went haywire.

I did a little more research and being my first ‚Äúadult‚Äù priced drone $300 was the limit. I saw this on a limited time deal and with some quick research I ordered it.

It‚Äôs been rock solid, after 22 loges flights even! We are building a house and it‚Äôs been so fun to take aerial views with it. We have used it at the lake and done follow me with in the boat. I am looking forward to using it on a camping trip this coming weekend.

I have tested a lot of features on this drone and they work. The return to home RTH works when you turn the transmitter off and when the battery gets too low. It usually lands within about 1 foot of the original departure point.

The photos have really good quality in good lighting. They get a little grainy in the lower light. If you happen to point it towards the sun or the lighted horizon it will over expose the camera and the land will be silhouetted. However just point the camera down and you can find a nice balance on the exposure.

The videos on calm days are really good. You have to be slow and smooth on the remote though. For example, slowly accelerate forward and it looks professional. If you let off to fast the drone with almost fly backwards to stop at that point throwing your camera upwards, so slowly decelerate and you will have nice videos.

Videos on windy days are jumpy. The camera is not on a gimbal to stabilize it. However if it‚Äôs not too windy you can use apps like iMovie and Windows Movie Maker, both free, to digitally stabilize the videos. It may crop some of the video and you will still see bumps as the wind rocks the drone, but it does a pretty decent job.

In the wind this drone is pretty amazing. You trade some battery life but around here the wind is usually 7-10 mph and this does quite well in that. Some days gusting to 15-20 and the drone handles them pretty well.

It is a lot of fun to fly.

Some cons though, when you get out to 150-200 meters away (their on screen app is all in meters) the video can get a little jumpy. It could be my iPhone 7 or the drone but at that distance you can barely see the drone anyway. The video on the SD card in the drone is smooth.

A couple pointers that aren‚Äôt real clear in the manual.

On a return to home, the drone will fly up to the altitude set in the app and return home. Make sure that‚Äôs above all your terrain, especially important working in valleys as this drone doesn‚Äôt have obstacle detection.

Second, when you have the drone circle around a point of interest fly the drone right over the point of interest, hit the video and photo buttons at the same time, then back the drone away to the radius distance away from the center you want and then hit the two buttons again and it will fly the circle around your point.

All in all, if you are getting a drone for fun and pretty cool pictures this drone fits the bill. I feel fairly safe flying it and am starting to trust it. My kids even fly it.

If you really want smooth videos look for a drone with a gimbal mount camera.

There are mods you can make to this drone but I‚Äôm sure they void the warranty. There are different lenses you can install and antenna upgrades, etc. I have seen them done online but I have not done them. I‚Äôm just putting this out there If you like to tinker around.

I will and would recommend this drone.
