title: A pleasure to fly, very well built.
text:
I've owned many remotes in the past. Helicopters, 8 and 4 prop drones. All seemed cheap and unimpressive. More like toys, and not very useful. I was hesitant to purchase this one. I am VERY glad that I did. The ROKU F11 Pro came in a well padded and thought out zippered case. Similar to a camera case. Inside, the drone, extra battery, extra props and the drones remote were all nestled safely. When removing the drone from its case, it was immediately noticeable that this was constructed of quality materials and made to last. The battery is easy to install and remove and is incorporated into the drones overall design. The arms fold neatly along the sides of the body, and the props fold out of the way. This design would allow a person to carry this drone in a large pocket if necessary, although I would suggest using its original case and perhaps a small backpack.
The set up of the drone is straight forward. With concise and clear instructions. After checking the battery levels in both the drone and its remote, I had the drone flying in about 2 minutes.
Speaking of controls, when the remote is folded out into "Flight mode" and my phone was placed in its holder, the remote felt as familiar as any PS4 or XBox controller. With the Left joystick you control Ascent and descent, and the direction that the drone is facing, while the Right joystick controls the forward and backward travel as well as the left and right drift.
From beginners to more advanced pilots, this drone will not disappoint. It has a very small learning curve. I took it through all of its capabilities, such as Follow Me, and laying out a course for it to follow. It performed perfectly.
If you are thinking of getting an inexpensive drone, and want one that has many of the features of much higher priced drones, then you should consider buying the ROKU F11 Pro.

title: Drone-tastic
text:
I recently purchased the Ruko F11 Pro Drone and I must say, it's an amazing product with exceptional customer service. I was a first-time drone user, and the guidebook and videos provided by Ruko made it incredibly simple and easy for me to learn how to fly the drone. The drone had outstanding wind resistance, and the homing beacon was spot on, which made it easier to return it to its original spot. The packaging is perfect for traveling with the drone, and the quality of the pictures and videos that I captured is impressive.

Unfortunately, after just a few runs in my backyard, my drone's wings caught a palm frond, and it crashed. As I checked the product box for any warranty information, I found out that I was outside the 90 days free warranty period. I was concerned about the repair costs and contacted Ruko product support to explain my situation. To my surprise, I received a response from a rep named Hailey within 24 hours, who offered me her expertise and a solution.

I was impressed with Hailey's knowledge of the product and her willingness to help me. Ruko's Customer Service team was amazing and patiently listened to my concerns and provided me with several options to repair my drone. I am grateful for Ruko team's outstanding customer service and the support that Ruko provided.

In conclusion, I would highly recommend the Ruko F11 Pro Drone to anyone who is interested in capturing amazing pictures and videos. The product is top-notch, and the customer service is exceptional. Thank you, Ruko, for providing such a great product

title: Aircraft does its own thing
text:
I‚Äôve had this drone for about a week. I have about eight hours of flight time with it. About 50% of the time it works great. Here are some of the issues when it‚Äôs not working.

1) sometimes the camera works, sometimes it doesn‚Äôt. You usually have to close the app and restart it several times before the camera will work.

2) sometimes in midflight the photo from the camera displayed on the phone will freeze. This is not from being too far away or from losing cell phone reception or from having an outdated, smart phone.

3) when you first receive the drone it‚Äôs in ‚Äúbeginner flight mode‚Äù basically what that does is while in flight the plane hits an invisible wall and bounces back to you. That invisible wall is only about 90 feet away. It‚Äôs gonna cause problems, because when it tries to zoom back to you, it might run into something as it‚Äôs flying in reverse as fast as it can to wherever you are.

4) this is the worst one of all. It has done this three times to me now. In mid flight for no reason it will literally do its own thing. It will start flying in circles or go from left to right, front to back, up and down. When doing this, it has ran directly into a tree and also decided to take it sell for a direct nose dive into the ground from about 60 feet up.

I‚Äôll be returning this as soon as possible.

Hello. I was excited to purchase your Ruko F11 Pro drone. I couldn‚Äôt wait to get it. It arrived yesterday and I immediately charged everything so I could play with it. However, I am having problems.

text:

I did notice that Ruko states, "The camera doesn't adjust fully forward‚Äî‚ÄîThis Camera unique design prevents the blades from affecting the picture or video so it will not look 100% forward. title: Great drone even for the beginner!
text: This drone is awesome!  I was very intimidated by just the idea of taking any drone into the air but this drone had a beginner setting to start you out and keep it close until you get comfortable.  After two 26 minute flights using the two included batteries I was ready for higher more distant flying.  I was not in a field like I probably should have been.  I was in my front yard navigating around power lines and poles.  You can set limits through the app or just take off.  You can read about the features and I can tell you that the features work as described.  Great pictures, great videos.  The videos and pictures that people are uploading don't do this drone justice.  You will need to pay up the $5 to the FAA to get a drone pilot license to legally fly this thing and learn the rules for flying .  Download the B4UFLY app for some good information.  Read and be responsible and you will be fine.

title: Waste of money
text: I bought one of these to take scenic videos.  I'm a beginner drone pilot.  Took it out to fly, had it at a park in the field, and somehow crashed it into a tree branch. Didn't know what I did wrong.  Bought and installed rotor covers.  Crashed into another tree, but no damage.  I was not even steering the drone toward the tree!  I was flying far enough from obstacles, I thought.  The third and final time I took it out, I used auto take off, and it did not stop where it was supposed to.  It kept going upward.  I was using the joystick to try and make it come back down, but it was not working.  It got up about 100', then just hovered.  I could not get it to go in any direction.  I was hitting the landing button, then using the joystick as well, in hopes that I could get it to come down.  Then, after a minute, it just descended.  Instead of hovering and landing softly, it did not slow down as much as it should have, causing a hard landing.  I read the remotes are an issue.  I'd steer clear.  I returned it.

title: The Ruko F11 Drone is awesome!
text:
I've had the most amazing experience with the Ruko F11! It isn't easy, it is not one of those turn it on and fly drones, the start up procedures need to be followed exactly. This drone is very powerful and flies very well in a light wind and returns to exactly where it took off. It has a full 30+ minutes of flight time. The photos are spectacularly clear! The video is amazing!
This drone is not for indoor use unless you have a vast area such as an arena, it is very powerful and creates wind that effects the flight when it nears furniture, for instance (ask me how I know). I did crash it a couple times because I tried taking off too close to the house and the indoor flying incident. It is durable and even though I chipped the props a little, it corrects itself and flies awesome. I haven't used my extra props (included with the item) yet and I don't crash anymore.
I previously had light-weight drones and they get blown away by the slightest breeze. This drone is substantial enough to fly in wind and as I said very powerful
It is not like the toy drones, it is complicated at start up because you link the WIFI with your Smartphone then procedures allow the gyros synchronize and the GPS to link with your phone. Then it is so responsive and easy to control. Honestly I was in too big of a hurry to follow the instructions and that resulted in the crashes.
After mastering the flying, then you learn to operate the HD camera. It allow you to adjust the lens angle, zoom and take action video while you fly.
This is a good purchase, I'm cheap so I hesitated to purchase this, but I am really glad I bought it. very worth the cost.

title: RUKO F11 will fly away and AMAZON will not replace it!
text:
This drone was highly rated! It has a navigation home button, the drone lost contact on a full battery and I‚Äôve searched for it for a week!

You lose the drone very easy and this time my app didn‚Äôt record the flight so no last known coordinates!

For $300 it‚Äôs not worth the terror of losing it and trying to find a needle in a haystack! I bought this from Amazon and they won‚Äôt replace it unless I find it! It‚Äôs not like I bought a bicycle and it was stolen, I put my expensive drone in flight on Christmas and it went on its merry way! That‚Äôs not what it‚Äôs advertised to do!!!

I‚Äôm hoping someone finds this drone so I can return it, must be defective!

Nonetheless, I wouldn‚Äôt buy a drone from Amazon, expensive drones need trackers! I think consumers need to know that RUKO F11 was not the quality drone as advertised and Amazon threw me under the bus! Buyer please beware that this drone will fly away and can‚Äôt be tracked!

title: This thing is awsome!
text: First time drone owner with limited flying experience....This thing is great.  Easy to configure to your phone.  Easy to fly.  Fun to fly. Not crash proof but seems pretty crash resistent.  I have a lot of trees and powerlines around my house.  Lots of obstacles to learn to fly around.  I typically learn to do things turning the power on and hitting the throttle.  This was no different.  Some advice...Read the adequate directions, be sure to do the set up calibration properly and when you do the gyro calibration BE SURE it's pretty level or it may fly toward a building and then when you try too recover it when it won't level out and it hits some powerlines and then you panic and kill the power and it falls 15 feet into a utility trailer, then the ground it will probably slightly break the landing gear and bang the props up.  It will most likely still fly after this but will be a little louder until you put some new props on it.  I have already placed the order.  Leave it on beginner settings so it won't get out of control until you get the hang of it.  Obviously the camera can take a hit as well and still work.  I haven't used the camera enough yet but from what I have seen so far it's pretty freaking awesome for the money. Have fun.

title: Very unstable
text: first and second flights the drone took off (as in just started flying away from me) and i was extremely lucky to get it back. third flight finally got it to hoover, but it was extremely unsteady, and would drift. I even tried it in a large warehouse with the GPS tuned off and no wind. it was calibrated on perfectly flat ground, and it still wouldn't hoover steady. I called teck support (who was easy to get ahold of, but all they said was you need a better signal) The one flight i managed to get a video, but the picture quality was really poor and super shaky. I had a buddy with a DJI fly do the same flight path on the at the same time and take the same video, his tuned out beautifully. other annoying thing is you need to do several calibrations on the drone EVERY TIME YOU TURN IT ON. I retuned mine. I did receive a full refund and purchased the DJI mini 2 SE. It was a few bucks more however is a vastly superior unit. No calibrations needed, flies great even on windy days. video quality is excellent and smooth as butter.

title: Good first drone
text: Had never had or flown a drone or RC aircraft so this was a bit of an experience for me initially. Using iPhone version of the SJRC app I initially had difficulty and it appeared that the remote might have been malfunctioning and not getting fully charged. After some very responsive troubleshooting with the company I was able to use their corrective method to get the controller to completely recognize battery status of drone and controller. For a first timer this thing is pretty cool and I have taken a few videos and still photos. I would say if you have never flown one of these things definitely leave the beginner configuration settings locked in and just practice practice practice, especially the landing if doing manual as the blades sit close to the ground and high grass will contact them. The app return to home feature and auto land are very decent functions, but I have not mastered the auto circle feature yet, nor have I tried the follow me feature. I only knocked it 1star because of the quirk with the app/controller interface reporting and the fact I could not get the rotate around an object feature to work correctly as of this review. It‚Äôs a decent value for the money so far with nine short flights (under 10min) under my belt.

text: [[VIDEOID:a7ad3263429d45d1448e04407631b8d7]] I have wanted a drone for several years. This year my wife told me to pick the one i wanted. I chose the F11 Pro after watching the videos I saw on line. It is very user friendly for a beginner. I have recommended this drone to family and friends

title: This F11 Pro Drone has the best features
text:
My experience with drones was very limited. Had one a few years ago, a very cheap one (about $70). By having it, I mean I had it for about 10 minutes. It then decided to keep flying up and away and was never seen again.

That made me a little reluctant to purchase another, especially to pay 3 times more. But in looking at the reviews and YouTube posts about the F11 Pro, I decided to give it a shot.

Boy I am glad I did. I practiced in a large open area and had no issues even on the first flights. Over the next couple of days I learned more and more and feel confident enough to take off in small clearings and with even continuous line-of-sight. All the described functions worked without a hitch and I took some great videos and photos over the local college. (No people or school during these pandemic times). With all the safeguards, I have no worries of watching my drone take a unscheduled flight to never-never land and me ending up with a controller and nothing else.

I highly recommend this drone to any level pilot, especially those beginners, like me, that want to be able to hang on to your investment.

title: Good Beginner Drone, Great Customer Service
text:
I bought the drone a year ago as a gift and it only got used a few times as the recipient was quite busy during that time. We brought it out again, and there was a problem where the propellers would hit the arms of the drone and crash itself.

Obviously this seemed like a manufacturing defect we did not catch on the first flight a year previous, and I requested a warranty repair. Even though my drone was a year out of the warranty, Cathy from the Ruko Team was able to greatly assist me and get me a replacement drone for very cheap. I just provided the flight logs to show it was not user error for the damages and was all set. Very swift, and professional customer service. The drone itself is great for beginners as flying drones takes practice and I would not suggest an expensive model for first time flyers.

title: Picked the right drone!
text:
I have never owned a drone. I spent weeks researching range, speed, frequencies, weight restrictions in places I want to go, camera types and more. It was not easy. I decided on folding drones for ease of carry and zoned in on a price I was comfortable with. After all this research I picked the Ruko F11 pro. And I couldn‚Äôt have been happier.

First, it got here to me a week faster than expected. I am stationed in Japan so I was quite amazed.

Second, I was concerned about my beginner skill to operate a drone. Most electronics you get a little card with operating web links on how to guides. But when I say my learning began on opening the box I wasn‚Äôt kidding. Inside the lid was a quick start guide. Opening the enclosed travel case was another guide. And then a full manual. Now this may not mean anything to most people. But knowing a company put that time into it made me a bit more confident.

Third. It‚Äôs a beautiful piece of hardware. Light. Stylish. Easy to understand how to fold/unfold, change the battery, insert a memory card, etc. the remote is comfortable in the hand and holds my iPhone 11 just fine.

Fourth. It was tested before shipping. Everything arrived charged. I get that all the time of ‚Äútested‚Äù but this company really does test each one. That‚Äôs such a time saver for them, and an extra thumbs up from me.

Fifth, the software on the phone is simple. But amazing. You don‚Äôt need a physics degree to understand it. At my age I don‚Äôt want to take a fundamental drone class, and with this one I don‚Äôt have to.

And finally, it works beautifully! No shaking issues, batteries last about the full time advertised. Camera has amazing pictures and videos. Easy to fly and fast to respond. It was worth much more than I paid for it. If you are on the fence about a drone, buy it. You won‚Äôt be disappointed.

title: Great product and solid technical support
text: This drone flies great, and the controls are super easy to grasp (except for the camera tilt).  The control/display app works on my Android flawlessly.  Pictures and videos are sharp and the on-board GPS system makes this drone very useful.  Landing using the automatic return-to-home button often misses the takeoff spot by a couple meters but that's still not bad.  I did have an issue when I flew too close to a wifi hotspot in my house, and the drone went haywire and crashed into the siding.  I contacted the company via email to get a replacement leg/foot that had cracked and was bent out of shape.  They promptly and courteously sent me the part I needed for free and I was able to install the new part in a few minutes.  I definitely enjoy this product, and the free extra battery I am promised for this feedback was an incentive to write this here, but did not influence my overall positive opinion.

title: Amazing drone
text: [[VIDEOID:e9132e1db94a75980d252dac12044144]] So, I have been flying, and crashing, drones for over a year. I started out with a little one from Harbour Freight.  After about two weeks, I watched it fly off out over the Gulf of Mexico. Since then, I‚Äôve had a Vivitar Skyview, bird took it out. Really. A Vivitar Phoenix, a piece of junk. A Potensic Atom. Fun drone, bad a$$ range but dainty. One small semi hard landing and all the sensors quit. Then a Walkera T210 mini. Was so excited to get it. But about a hundred and fifty yards into my first flight this little drone took off. I never seen a drone move so quickly. It would not respond.  It hit the hard deck very very hard. Totaled it. The drone took about 1 1/2 hours to bind to remote to begin with. I guess what I‚Äôm trying to get to is this. I got this Ruko F11 Pro and right out of the box this thing was in the air in 10 minutes. Not counting the charge battery time of just about 4 hours for remote and two batteries. This drone is of professional level yet a beginner could fly it easily. I live on the Texas coast and the wind is pretty much always blowing. Oh yeah, did I mention the Holy Stone 360 or something like that. I could never fly it because of the wind. This Ruko drone has been up to 395ish feet in the air, over the Lavaca Bay, in winds in excess of 35 mph!!! Crazy? Nope. True? Yes. I believe that Ruko has outdone all othe drones in its price gap. Hands down. The range on it is true. Will be getting range extenders eventually. I like to take it as far as it‚Äôll go. It‚Äôs also durable. I‚Äôve landed kinda hard a few times because of the wind. Thank you Ruko!! For making such a killer drone at an amazing price!!!

title: The drone works really good!
text:
The drone is really funny, I got it by Wednesday and I didn't have the chance to try it till two days ago.
So the drone I think for the price which is 299.99$ is an awesome product, the brushless motors which is a great improvement that you see on dji drones and other ones close to that gap, the camera is clean, pictures 2k, videos in 1080p, the 90¬∞ angle of the camera and also the button for the speed of the drone simply makes the difference, they're so many features that in my opinion they're good but is stuff that I'm never gonna use, let's be clear boys, you want a drone that can take pictures and videos on high resolution and also be very fast, this little guy goes at almost 27 mph, the signal is good, and the controller is really comfortable, plus the two batteries that last 28 min each one and the case that goes within, makes you wanna go outside and try it on a field.
Now the bad thing about this is that the camera doesn't have the 3-axis, that means your videos are gonna be a bit shaky if is windy, the batteries take a little too much to charge at they're fullest (almost 5h if used all of it) The connection in the app sometimes gets lost, when is about this whole recording thing, sometimes I have him at H: height 43 or 44 (the limit is 120) and the transmission gets kinda bugged or slow or just lost the connection. To be honest there's nothing you can do to fix this, I have a Samsung s9 and this happen sometimes maybe is just with android I still have to try with my friend's phone (she haves an Iphone 8) to see how's gonna be the behavior.
Guys this is a cheap drone and it haves a lot of good things specially the motors, with the bad stuff I think in my opinion is just stuff that can get fixed, updates for the app, another battery, and just fly when is not windy, the drone itself works perfectly so if you're like me that I always saw drones copters and those kind of little guys on internet and always wanted to try for real, this is your choice, just read the instructions, be aware of what you're doing, flight safe and respect your surroundings.

text: The F-11 pro being heavier and more solidly built makes it fly better in wind. Its a solid, rock steady and relatively fast quad. The wide angle camera makes FPV w/goggles much better. Flies easy.....battery life 15 to 28 minutes depending on what you are doing.

text: Brought this to several people with more cpu skill's than myself. Used android and I-phones to get it working and it would not leave the ground. Tried to contact the company itself by e-mail with no reply. It was a gift and not opened for several months. So no returning it. Waisted money.

title: Ruko f11 pro
text: I loved the drone it's very nice flies fantastic and its fast, but I had one sent and everything worked great besides the camera once u aim it down while it's in the air it would not go back up at all I had to land it turn it off and manually put the camera back up so I had them send me another one and what do u know the same thing was happening to that one you can hear the motor trying to go back up but it wouldnt so I wasnt doing it a third time so I upgraded to the ruko f11 gim I love this thing it's worth the extra money trust me.

title: Instant quality and fun
text: Finally a drone that has it all at a great price! I have been through 4 drones before this one (higher and lower in price, )and have either lost them or the photos and videos were terrible. Right out of the box I was comfortable and thrilled with this drone. I already have more quality photos and videos with this one than all of my previous ones. Highly recommend this not only for beginners but for anyone who wants to have some fun and get awesome results.

title: Great drone
text: Awesome product works as advertised

title: Bang for the buck even under non conventional use
text:
Overall this has been a great investment and I would not hesitate to purchase another. For the average user this drone will perform well meeting or surpassing most people‚Äôs needs. I have had this drone for a week now. Overall it has been good with a few minor issues.

First off before I get to deep into this my experience tends to be different than most. I work in the fixed wireless business or wireless internet service provider field so issues that I run into are different than your normal user.

1. I have found that in high wireless noise areas the drone drops the wireless connection between itself and your phone/tablet. If you allow for the drone to settle for a minute or so it tends to find a clear channel and you can continue on with flying. I have had no issues with the drone losing connection to the controller in this situation and can continue to fly but I have to keep a visual on the drone (maybe this is something they can fix in the future so you can connect to the controller vs. the drone).

2.The GPS is a bit off when you allow the drone to return to home with the feature on the controller. My drone tends to average about 20 foot from the original launch point when using this feature. However in an emergency this is fine. I have found that the drone is super simple to fly and completing take off and landings without the extra buttons is way easier to work with.

3. The camera is great and performs surprisingly well. I do wish it was gimbal instead due to the fact that I use it for taking pictures of my broadcast equipment at elevated heights (150 to 300 foot) so wind can be a problem when trying to get Detailed stills or video. Patients is the key tho.

4. Lastly is the case. It has been great for organization and I was able to store an extra battery inside with no issues (I can store 2 in the battery slot and I leave one in the drone). However I have found with slight pressure on the lid you can turn the drone on while it is in the bag. (It just powers up it does not try to operate you have to use the remote to make it functional) This does cause the battery to drain so if you are not careful you can loose some valuable flight time. A relocate of the power button would solve this issue.

title: I am very pleased and thankful for the ruko drone team
text: I had an issue with the ap, turned out my tablet was way too old for being even able to scan a qr code, I love this drone and wanted to get it flying asap, but it took a bit of time till i could get a good phone to use that was not 50 years old, lol.  ruko was totally working with me and making sure i was a satisfied ruko owner.  I wish i could give ten stars instead of five. Thank you ruko team!!!!!!
